<html>

<head>
<title>Humanities</title>
</head>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu">
<body>
<h1 align=center>Rockford College<br>
Department of Humanities</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Index</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/academic/catalog/human/human.htm#overview">Overview</a> </li>
<li><a href="/academic/catalog/human/human.htm#require">Requirements</a> </li>
<li><a href="/academic/catalog/human/courses.htm">Course Offerrings</a> </li>
</ul>
<hr>
<a name="overview"></a>
<h3>Overview</h3>
<p><br>
The Bachelor of Arts degree program in humanities enables students to study a particular period, 
theme, or topic through the humane disciplines. The humanities major extends the general education 
requirements of the college to allow students to pursue further work in the arts, history, literature, 
philosophy, and foreign language.
<P>
 The major includes a core program of required courses and an 
upper-level special program. The special program, which students will design in consultation with 
appropriate faculty members, may focus on a particular period -- the later Middle Ages, for 
example, or the early Twentieth Century -- or on a particular topic such as American romanticism 
or Renaissance humanism. <P>



<a name="require"></a>
<h3>Degree Requirements</h3>
<pre>

<strong>Core program -- 29 hours</strong>

Two survey courses in literature in a foreign language

Fren 301 Survey of French Literature I and
Fren 302 Survey of French Literature II     }                6 hours or
Ger 301 Survey of German Literature I and
Ger 302 Survey of German Literature II }                     6 hours or
Span 301 Survey of Spanish Literature I and
Span 302  Survey of Spanish Literature II   }                6 hours or
Two appropriate 300-level courses in Greek or Latin          6 hours

Clas 123 Greek Civilization or
Clas 124 Roman Civilization  }                               3 hours 
Eng 201 Survey of English Literature I and 
Eng 202 Survey of English Literature II     }                6 hours 
Phil 317 Classical and Medieval Philosophy or 
Phil 318 Modern Philosophy or     }                          3 hours
Rel 212 History of Christianity
Hist 101 Western Civilization I and
Hist 102 Western Civilization II  } or                       8 hours
Hist 102 Western Civilization II and
Hist 103 Western Civilization III 
Note: Students in the Honors Program in Liberal Arts may substitute 
appropriate Liberal Arts courses.

One of the following:

Art 245 History of Western Art I                             3 hours
Art 246 History of Western Art I                             3 hours
Dan 211 History of Dance                                     3 hours
Music 217 Music History I                                    3 hours
Music 218 Music History II                                   3 hours
TA 384 Theatre History I                                     3 hours
TA 385 Theatre History II                                    3 hours
</pre>


<P>
<strong>Special program -- 16 hours</strong>
<P>
A student must complete a minimum of 16 semester hours of 300- and 
400-level course work in a definable and humane field, with courses 
chosen in consultation with the humanities major advisor and faculty 
members from the student's fields of interest. The program must be 
approved by the humanities major advisor.


<P>
<strong>Senior project -- 4 hours</strong>
<P>
No later than mid-term of the semester before students' senior 
projects, they are responsible for setting up a committee of two or 
more faculty members with competence in the student's chosen field 
and choosing one of them as chairman. The committee must be
approved by the humanities major advisor and the dean of the college.
<P>
No later than the end of the semester preceding students' project work, 
they must prepare-- in consultation with the committee -- a written 
plan for the project, and send it to the humanities major advisor and 
the dean of the college for approval.
<P>
Ordinarily, students undertake an independent cross-disciplinary 
senior project for four semester hours under the instructor most directly 
concerned. If students are prepared properly in a particular field, they 
may substitute a regular Senior Seminar in an appropriate department 
with written approval from the humanities advisor, the dean of the
college, and the course instructor.



<hr>
<p><a href="http://www.rockford.edu">Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</a> </p>
