<HEAD>

<TITLE>Honors Program in Liberal Arts</TITLE>

<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">


</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>Rockford College<BR>
Honors Program in Liberal Arts</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<H2>Index</H2>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/academic/catalog/honors/honors.htm#overview">
Overview</A>
<LI><A HREF="/academic/catalog/honors/honors.htm#require">
Requirements</A>
</UL>
<HR>
<A NAME="overview"></A>
<H3>Overview</H3>
<PRE>
  The purpose of the Honors Program in Liberal Arts is to
encourage excellence through a program of special courses, broad
distribution requirements, and extracurricular events. 
  The special courses, which introduce students to the
development of Western civilization from the ancient Greeks and
Hebrews down to the present, are developed and taught by a
course director and another faculty member from a complementary
discipline. Each course approaches its period through broad,
interdisciplinary historical studies of art, literature,
philosophy, science, religion, and politics. Guest lectures and
other presentations by visiting scholars are scheduled
frequently. 
  The broad distribution requirements encourage contact with as
many departments as possible outside students' majors.
Extracurricular events, both academic and social, extend
students' studies beyond the classroom and enable them to form
those friendly relationships with faculty that characterize
liberal studies at their best.
  To be invited to participate in the program as entering
freshmen, students should have a composite score of at least 27
on the ACT or appropriate scores on the SAT, have graduated in
the top 10 percent of their senior class in high school, or
merit special consideration.
  New transfer students must have had at least a 3.35 GPA (B) in
the two most recent college semesters; students with only one
semester of college work must have had a 3.35 GPA during that
semester.
  To enter after one semester or more at Rockford College,
students must have a cumulative 3.0 GPA. If they do not meet the
ordinary standards, students may apply for special consideration
and may be admitted at the discretion of the chair of the Honors
Program in Liberal Arts. To continue in the program and complete
it successfully, students must maintain a cumulative GPA of at
least 3.0.
</PRE>
<A NAME="require"></A>
<H3>Degree requirements</H3>
<STRONG>Special courses</STRONG>
<PRE>
  One Liberal Arts course is offered each semester, beginning
with Liberal Arts 201 and proceeding in chronological order.
Students must take all four to complete the program (though not
necessarily in order), and must achieve an average of 3.0 in all
four with no grade below "C" in any one.

LA 201 The Ancient World                                    4 hours 
LA 202 The Middle Ages                                      4 hours 
LA 203 Renaissance and Reformation                          4 hours 
LA 204 The Enlightenment and the Modern World               4 hours
</PRE>

<STRONG>Distribution requirements</STRONG>
<PRE>
Arts (at least one studio course and course work
in history of art, music, or theatre)                        8 hours 
Language and Literature                                     12 hours 
Science and Mathematics                                     12 hours 
Social Sciences                                             12 hours                                              
</PRE>

<STRONG>Foreign language requirement</STRONG>
<PRE>
  All students in the program must complete study of a foreign
language through the 203 level (in Latin and Greek, through 204)
or demonstrate by examination that they have attained that level.
</PRE>

<STRONG>Special events</STRONG>
<PRE>
  Films, concerts, lectures, trips, dinners, etc., will be
organized to complement the core courses.
</PRE>
