<STRONG>Minor in Religious Studies -- 18 hours</STRONG>
  Religious Studies is an interdisciplinary minor administered by
the Chair of the Division of Arts and Humanities. Students may
take courses with Religious Studies numbers or courses in other
departments which are listed below the Religious Studies
courses. At least nine hours of the minor in Religious Studies
must carry the Religious Studies designation, and at least one
course must be taken at the 300 level. Students must take at
least three courses totalling at least nine hours at Rockford
College and earn a 2.0 average in the minor.
