<head>
<title>Sociall Science</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<base href="http://www.rockford.edu/">
</head>

<body>
<h1 align=center>Rockford College<br>
Department of Social Science</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Index</h2>
<ul>

<li><a href="/academic/catalog/social/social.htm#overview">Overview</a> </li>
<li><a href="/academic/catalog/social/social.htm#career">Career Opportunities</a> </li>
<li><a href="/academic/catalog/social/social.htm#require">Requirements</a> </li>

</ul>
<hr>

<a name="overview"></a><h3>Overview</h3>
<p>
With the Social Sciences Divisional Major, students have a certain degree of flexibility in 
selecting a program of study from among the disciplines in the division. However, students
 must take a senior seminar in one of the disciplines, and the major must be approved by
 the chairs of the division and of the department in which students will take the Senior Seminar. 
<P>
At least 30 hours of the major must be taken at Rockford College, and at least six
 of the courses must be taken at the 300- or 400-level. Students may take a
 Bachelor of Arts or Bachelor of Science degree in the divisional<BR>
major.
<br>
<br>
</p>
<A NAME="career"></a><h3>Career Opportunities</h3>
The divisional program leading to the bachelor's degree in the social
 studies may be a desirable alternative to one of the departmental
 programs if students plan careers in elementary or secondary teaching,
 social work, work in governmental administration, or work in foreign commerce. 
<br>
<br>
</p>
<a name="require"></a><h3>Degree Requirements</h3>
<pre><strong>Major requirements (B.A.) -- 42 hours</strong> 

One introductory course from each of these disciplines:
Anthropology and Sociology 3-4 hours
Economics                                 3-4 hours
Political Science                      3-4 hours
Psychology                               3-4 hours
One course in History              3-4 hours
Two additional courses in each of two of the above disciplines  12-16 hours
Five additional courses in a third discipline from the above listed disciplines 15-20 hours
    (Note: one of the five must be Senior Seminar -- 4 hours)

Major requirements (B.S.) -- 42 hours
All requirements for the Bachelor of Arts Degree

Supporting requirements (B.S. only) -- 3-8 hours
One course in Statistics or Computer Science     3-4 hours.
One course in methodology                                   0-4 hours
    (Note: The course in methodology may be one taken above for the major.)                                                        
</pre>
<BR>
<STRONG>Teacher certification 6-12</strong><BR>
<P>
Students interested in becoming certified to teach the Social Sciences at the
 secondary level must complete the Social Sciences major degree requirements,
 a minor in secondary education, and additional general education requirements 
for state certification. In the Social Sciences subject areas, students must have
 8 hours in each subject they want to teach. Additionally, any student interested 
in teaching history needs 16 hours in history. For further information, see the
 Education section of this catalog.

<hr>
<p><a href="http://www.rockford.edu">Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</a> </p>
