</UL>
<HR>

<A NAME="faculty"></A>
<H3>Faculty</H3>

<PRE>
Bertil Nyman, MBA Director
Ray Baker
Dr. Gerald Caton
Henry Espensen
Robert Evans
Jeffrey Fahrenwald (on leave, 1996-97)
Dr. Masoud Moallem
James Millikin
Michael Mrkvicka
Dr. Fred Rezazadeh
Dr. Susan Whealler
Robert Von der Ohe
</PRE>

<A NAME="overview"></A>
<H3>Overview</H3>

<PRE>
All students interested in pursuing a Master of Business 
Administration  degree  at Rockford College must be aware 
of and comply with these  general regulations.   Any questions 
about these regulations should be addressed to the academic  
advisor or the Director of the MBA Program.

*Students must maintain a 3.00 GPA in all required graduate course 
 work attempted in the MBA program.  Prerequisite MBA courses 
 do not count as part of the required courses.

*Students are expected to enroll in at least one course every school 
 year (fall semester through summer session).  Failure to comply 
 will result in students' dismissal from the program.  To be readmitted, 
 students must reapply and follow the rules, regulations and requirements 
 in effect at the time of reapplication.

*Students must have signed Plans of Study on file before they will be 
 allowed to register for courses.  Plans must be developed in consultation 
 with their advisors before the pre-registration period.

*Students must complete all requirements for the degree within five 
 years of  the date of admission to the degree program.
</PRE>
<A NAME="require"></A>
<H3>Degree Requirements</H3>

<PRE>
<STRONG>Prerequisites</STRONG>

Prerequisites in economics, accounting, business finance, statistics and 
mathematical analysis must be completed within the past 10 years with a 
grade of C or better.

BA 501 Mathematical Analysis for Management -- 3 hours
BA 502 Survey of the Principles of Economics -- 3 hours
BA 518 Business Finance -- 3 hours
BA 524 Accounting Concepts -- 3 hours
Math 223 Beginning Statistics -- 3 hours or
Math 224 Elements of Statistics -- 4 hours

<STRONG>Required Courses -- 10 hours</STRONG>


No more than three of the ten required courses taken before admission to 
the program can be counted toward the MBA degree.

BA 503 Managerial Economics -- 3 hours
BA 504 Business and the National Economy -- 3 hours
BA 510 Legal Environment of Business -- 3 hours
BA 530 Managerial Accounting and Control* -- 3 hours
BA 540 Financial Management -- 3 hours
BA 550 Management Theory -- 3 hours
BA 560 Marketing -- 3 hours
BA 580 Introduction to Business Research* -- 3 hours
BA 590 Business Writing and Communication* -- 3 hours
BA 696 Business Planning and Strategies -- 3 hours

*Must be completed within the first 15 hours of required course work.

<STRONG>Elective courses -- 6 hours</STRONG>

Only students admitted to the MBA degree program who have completed at 
least seven of the 10 required courses may take 600-level courses.

BA 641 Investment Management -- 3 hours
BA 650 Production Management -- 3 hours
BA 651 Organizational Behavior -- 3 hours
BA 652 International Business -- 3 hours
BA 654 Human Resource Management -- 3 hours
BA 660 Consumer Behavior -- 3 hours
BA 661 Promotion Policies & Management -- 3 hours
BA 670 International Trade & Financial Management -- 3 hours
BA 680 Information Systems -- 3 hours

<A NAME="cpa"></A>
<H3>MBA/CPA Preparation Program</H3>
<STRONG>Required courses -- 39 hours</STRONG>
BA 503 Managerial Economics -- 3 hours
BA 504 Business and the National Economy -- 3 hours
BA 505 Business Law I -- 4 hours
BA 506 Business Law II -- 4 hours
BA 530 Managerial Accounting and Control -- 3 hours
BA 540 Financial Management -- 3 hours
BA 550 Management Theory -- 3 hours
BA 560 Marketing -- 3 hours
BA 580 Introduction to Business Research -- 3 hours
BA 590 Business Writing and Communication -- 3 hours
BA 690 Business Planning & Strategies -- 3 hours
Acct 546* Advanced Accounting -- 4 hours
Acct 547* Auditing Theory & Practice  -- 4 hours

* Intermediate Accounting is a prerequisite for Acct 546 and 547.

<A NAME="cj"></A>
<STRONG>MBA/Criminal Justice Program</STRONG>

In response to the need for management professionals throughout the 
criminal justice system and as a complement to the Rockford College 
undergraduate program in criminal justice, the Master of Business 
Administration program includes a track to educate men and women 
for professional positions in law enforcement, the courts, and a broad 
range of public service fields. 

This flexible program requires a carefully formulated plan of study in 
both Business Administration and Criminal Justice course work, developed 
in conjunction with the academic advisor. Contact the Office of Graduate 
Studies for more information as to specific requirements.

</PRE>

