<HEAD>
<title>KEEP THIS FOR EASY REFERENCE </title>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<h2>KEEP THIS FOR EASY REFERENCE </h2>
     
     <h2>IMPORTANT THINGS TO REMEMBER DURING YOUR YEARS AT ROCKFORD COLLEGE</h2>
     
     <pre>(This is intended for all full-time and part-time undergraduate,
     students who are pursuing a degree, unless otherwise noted)
     </pre>
     <ul>
     <LI>All students must stop by the Business Office on or before 4 p.m. on the
     first day    of class each semester to get their ID cards validated and to and
     make arrangements    for payment of their tuition.  If you do not do this,
     your registration will be     purged and you will have to pay a $25 late fee
     to be re-registered.<BR><BR>    
     <LI>All students must make sure their health records have been received by
     the Lang     Health Center.  If you do not do this, you will have a "hold"
     placed on your        records and you will not be able to pre-register for the
     following semester until    that "hold" has been removed.<BR><BR>     
     <LI>All full-time undergraduate students must attend two forum series events
     each         semester.  The College Forum Series is a graduation requirement
     and failure to      attend two events each semester will prevent you from
     graduating.  If you are unable    to attend two events, you can listen to the
     tapes which are kept in the library and    write a 200-word paper.<BR><BR>     
     <LI>If you want to transfer a course into Rockford College once you have
     matriculated    at Rockford College you must have that course approved before
     you take it.  There    is a form called "Transfer of Credit" which must be
     filled out and signed by the    appropriate department chair.<BR><BR>     
     <LI>All undergraduate students, upon completion of the freshman English
     requirement     (ENGL 112 or the equivalent), must fulfill the Upper Division
     Requirement in        Writing or Public Speaking (UDRWOPS).  You can do this
     in one of three ways:  
       a) written exam, b) speech, c) course.  If you intend to satisfy the
     requirement    by taking an exam, you must do so by the semester in which 75
     hours are achieved.    If you do not pass the appropriate examination by the
     time 75 hours are achieved,    then you must register for an UDRWOPS course
     recommended by the UDRWOPS Committee.    Students who transfer in 75 hours or
     more must pass an examination during their first semester at Rockford
     College or register for an UDRWOPS course recommended    by the UDRWOPS
     Committee.<BR><BR>     
     <LI>In the second semester of your sophomore year you will need to file a
     Declaration    of Major.  Simply putting a preferred major on your application
     for admission is    not the same thing.  You will need to do this before you
     can pre-register for       classes for your junior year.  If you do not do
     this ahead of time you will be      required to sign a waiver form stating
     that the Office of Registration will not be    responsible if you do not
     graduate on time.<BR><BR>     
     <LI>Graduation applications are due according to the following schedule:
<PRE> 
June 15 for students completing requirements in the summer         
September 15 for students completing requirements in the fall      
Second Friday in December for students completing requirements in May
</PRE>
</ul>
<pre>
*     *     *     *     *     *     *     *     *     *     *     *     *      
</pre 
     <P>Any forms you may need can be obtained from the Office of Registration on
     the first floor of Burpee Center.</P>
     


<HR>
