<HEAD>
<TITLE>Frequently Asked Questions</TITLE>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">                       
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1> 
<hr>
<b> How do I contact the Office of Alumni Relations?</b><br><br>

The Office of Alumni Relations can be reached by mail, telephone, 
E-mail, or fax.<br><br>

<center>
<b>Regular Mail:</b><br>
Office of Alumni Relations<br>
Rockford College<br>
5050 East State Street<br>
Rockford IL 61108<br><br>

<b>Telephone</b>:  815-226-4080<br>

<b>Fax</b>:  815-226-4119<br>
<b>E-mail</b>: <a href="mailto:alumni@rockford.edu">
alumni@rockford.edu</a><br><br>
</center>
<hr>
<b> Does Rockford College offer E-mail accounts to alumni?</b><br><br>

At the present time, the college does not offer internet access to alumni.<br>
<hr>
<b>How do I contact an old friend from Rockford College?</b><br><br>

The Office of Alumni Relations is delighted to help you find your friends from
your days on campus.  However, at the same time, the college must protect the
privacy of all its alumni.<p>

If you would like to contact a friend, we ask that you submit your request in
writing.  The Office of Alumni Relations will acknowledge your request and
forward your letter of inquiry to the person whose address is being requested.
For each person you are looking to contact, please include a stamped, unsealed
envelope with your name and return address in the top left corner.  This envelope
will be used to forward your request to your friend.<p>
<center>
Send your requests to:<br>

Office of Alumni Relations<br>
Rockford College<br>
5050 East State Street<br>
Rockford IL  61108<br><br>
</center>
