<P><BR clear="left">
<A HREF="#The Program">The Program</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Coach">The Coach</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#SCHEDULE">The Schedule</A></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<H2><A NAME="The Program"></A>The Program</H2>

<P>Regent baseball is very respected in the Midwest. Playing a perennially
rugged schedule that includes Cartage, Aurora, North Central, Loras, and
U-Wisconsin-Whitewater makes the Regents stronger. &quot;There are no cupcakes
in the Central Region&quot; states coach Langston. Each year the team begins
the season in Florida playing in Ft. Myers to prepare for the northern
season. </P>

<P>Most importantly, Regent Baseball players graduate on time, have a great
baseball experience and get a quality education. </P>

<H2>Bill Langston, Head <A NAME="Coach"></A>Coach</H2>

<P>Bill Langston has spent 16 years at the helm of the Regents, winning
over 300 games. His offensive philosophy is &quot;run, run, run.&quot;
The Regents enjoy this exciting brand of baseball that causes fits for
their opponents. &quot;We aren't always the biggest or the strongest team
on the field, but you better be prepared for us&quot; he is proud of saying
to anyone who will listen. Langston learned his game from his father in
high school, and baseball coaching legends Danny Litwiler(FSU), Duffy Bass
and &quot;Itchy&quot; Jones who he either played for or coached with. A
strong believer in the NCAA III philosophy of &quot;participation for all&quot;
Langston tailors his program to be a quality experience for all of his
athletes </P>

<P><A NAME="COACH"></A><BR>
</P>

