<P><BR clear="left">
<A HREF="#The Program">The Program</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Mike Duenser, Head Coach">The Coach</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Schedule Fall '96">The Schedule</A></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<H2><A NAME="The Program"></A>The Program</H2>

<P>The Regents enter the second year under Coach Mike Duenser with several
new faces and a good compliment of returners. Excitement abounds with the
new height - 7'1 &quot; Adnan Krupalija, and 6'6&quot; transfer Jason Warner,
who should become an instant force in the lineup. The Regents open in Wartburg,
Iowa, host the Rockford Classic, and also play in the Elmhurst Holiday
tourney. NIIC competition begins January 6 at Conqordia-River Forest. </P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2><A NAME="Mike Duenser, Head Coach"></A>Mike Duenser, Head Coach</H2>

<P>W. Michael Duenser begins his second year as the Head Coach of the Regents
and has already served notice on the area and the conference that the Regents
will improve, by bringing his first recruiting class in that includes the
college's first seven-footer. </P>

<P>Duenser's roots are in eastern Iowa, where he coached at Clarke College
and the University of Dubuque before joining the Regents. His enthusiasm
and aggressiveness reflect a level of energy that is contagious and will
bring the Regents to a very competitive level. </P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

