<p><a href="#Schedule Fall '96">The Schedule</a></p>

<p><br>
</p>

<h2><a name="The Program">The Program</a></h2>

<p>The 1996 edition met the challenge of the double conference in
style, winning the N.I.I.C. outright and tying for first place in the
NIIGC before losing a playoff to St. Francis. Seniors Jason
Nordvall and Dan Koenings, along with Junior Shanin Solt, led a
veteran squad. The spring portion of the schedule will include
invitationals around the Midwest. </p>

<h2><a name="Richard Bromley, Head Coach">Richard Bromley, Head
Coach</a></h2>

<p>A veteran coach, Richard Bromley brings over 30 years of
experience to the Regent linksters. His expertise was acknowledged
by his being selected &quot;Coach of the Year&quot; in the
N.I.I.C. this fall. In addition to coaching, Mr. Bromley is professor
of physical education at Rockford College. </p>

<p><a name="COACH"><br>
</a></p>

