</ROWS></TBODY></table>

<p><br clear="left">
<a href="#The Program">The Program</a></p>

<p><a href="#Rasim Secerovic, Head Coach">The Coach</a></p>

<p><a href="#Schedule Fall '96">The Schedule</a></p>

<p><br>
<br>
</p>

<h2><a name="The Program">The Program</a></h2>

<p>With the departure of four All-NIIC players and the loss of 6
other players, Coach Secerovic is looking for others on the team
to step up and take control of the situation. Senior Ron Collins
(Cincinnati, OH), a 1996 All-NIIC player, and Junior Peter
Judkins (St. Louis, MO) are two of the players that Secerovic is
counting on to carry the 1996 Regents. The return of Senior
Biniam Girmay (Dewitt, MI) should lead the defense and try to
keep the goalie from being very busy. Secerovic is also looking
for someone to take over in goal since the loss of both of last
year's goalies to other schools. </p>

<h2><a name="Rasim Secerovic, Head Coach">Rasim Secerovic, Head Coach</a></h2>

<p>The 1996 edition of the Regent soccer team is a new look one.
With new Head Coach Rasim Secerovic and the loss of all four of
the Regents All-NIIC team members, the 1996 season looks to be
one of many surprises. Coach Secerovic brings many years of
professional soccer experience with him from Bosnia, where he
played and coached for the majority of his life until he defected
with his junior national basketball team to the United States in
the early 1990's. Since that time, Secerovic has been an
assistant basketball coach for the Regents. </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

