<p><br clear="left">
<a href="#The Program">The Program</a></p>

<p><a href="#Chris Bowser, Head Coach">The Coach</a></p>

<p><a href="#Schedule Spring '97">The Schedule</a></p>

<p><br>
<br>
</p>

<h2><a name="The Program">The Program</a></h2>

<p>Rockford Mens Tennis which was once a very strong program has
struggled over the past five seasons. Dwindling numbers have hampered
the effort to bring the program back to prominence. The 1995-96
season concluded April 22 with a dual meet record of 5-3.
Anticipation lingers for the 1997 season. </p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2><a name="Chris Bowser, Head Coach">Chris Bowser, Head Coach</a></h2>

<p>Chris Bowser is an energetic, young coach who is dedicated to
bringing Rockford Tennis back from the dead and making it a power
in the NIIC Conference once again. A 1995 graduate of the
University of Northern Iowa, Boswer is also the Assistant Men's
Basketball Coach and also pursuring his master's degree in Education. </p>

<p><br>
</p>

