</CAPTION>

<TR>
<TD align="center"><IMG SRC="rcsign3.gif" HEIGHT=142 WIDTH=162></TD>

<TD align="center">
<H1>Men's and Women's<BR>
Swimming<BR>
Rockford College </H1>
</TD>

<TD><IMG SRC="campus1.gif" HEIGHT=98 WIDTH=261></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><BR clear="left">
<BR>
<A HREF="#The Program">The Program</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#David Mcdevitt, Head Coach">The Coach</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Schedule">The Schedule</A></P>

<P><BR>
</P>

<H2><A NAME="The Program"></A>The Program</H2>

<P>Rockford College Swimming has a long tradition of excellence in the
water and has produced 22 All-Americans. These include both men and women,
swimmers and divers, national record holders and national champions. Rockford
College will provide you an opportunity to excel in the sport of swimming
while earning an education. It is an opportunity for you be a big fish
in a small pond . If you love the sport of swimming and want to receive
a excellent education, take a good look at Rockford College! </P>

<H2><A NAME="David Mcdevitt, Head Coach"></A>David McDevitt, Head Coach</H2>

<P>The Regents swimmers are coached by David McDevitt, an American Swimming
Coaches Association Level 5 coach, its highest ranking. Coach McDevitt
took over the program from Coach Dick Bromley after 33 years at the helm.
Coach McDevitt comes to Rockford College with over 15 years of experience
in coaching swimming. He has coached every level of swimmer from the swimmers
just learning to swim, to elite athletes who have finished as high as third
in the nation and have been ranked internationally. Coach McDevitt hopes
to build the program back to its glory years of the late 70's and early
80's. Coach McDevitt is searching for those individuals who love the sport
of swimming and would like to continue it while getting an excellent education.
His philosophy has always been to strive to improve your times while having
fun. He expects his swimmers to work hard in the pool and in the classroom.
&quot;I believe that every student -athlete should strive for excellence.
As a coach, that is what I will try to give to you and all I ask is that
you return the same,&quot; he states.<BR>
<BR>
</P>

