<A HREF="#PROGRAM">The Program</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#COACH">The Coach</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Schedule Spring '97">The Schedule</A></P>

<P><BR>
</P>

<H2><A NAME="PROGRAM"></A>The Program</H2>

<P>Following the 1996 season that saw them compile a school record 22 wins,
the Regents expect to challenge for the NIIC Championship. Four All NIIC
players return for their senior year, led by Kim Schubert, who also earned
All-Midwest Region honors last spring. A trip to Ft. Myers, Florida starts
a season that could bring the Regents their first NIIC title.</P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2><A NAME="COACH"></A>Kristyn King, Head Coach</H2>

<P>Kristyn King graduated from Rockford in 1988, playing four years of
softball . She served as the softball graduate assistant at Northwest Missouri
State before returning to her alma mater. She has steadily built the Regents
into one of the strong Midwest programs. In 1996, Coach King was selected
&quot;Coach of the Year&quot; by the N.I.I.C. She also is the Assistant
Athletic Director at Rockford. </P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

