<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<table border="2">
<tbody><rows>    <tr>
        <td align="center"><img src="rcsign3.gif" width="162"
        height="142"></td>
        <td align="center"><h1>Women's Soccer<br>
        Rockford College</h1>
        </td>
        <td><img src="campus1.gif" width="261" height="98"></td>
    </tr>
</ROWS></TBODY></table>

<p><br clear="left">
<a href="#The Program">The Program</a></p>

<p><a href="#Lee Carley, Head Coach">The Coach</a></p>

<p><a href="#Schedule Fall '96">The Schedule</a></p>

<h2><a name="The Program">The Program</a></h2>

<p>The Rockford College women's soccer program is going into its
7th season. Over the past two seasons the Lady Regents have gone
19-18-3. During the 1995 season, which was the inaugural for women's
soccer in the Northern Illinois Intercollegiate Conference,
Rockford finished at 5-3. In 1996, RC will be pointing toward its
first ever NIIC championship. The Lady Regents play a competitive
NCAA Division III schedule made up of teams from Iowa, Minnesota,
Wisconsin, Indiana and Illinois. </p>

<h2><a name="Lee Carley, Head Coach">Lee Carley, Head Coach</a></h2>

<p>Lee Carley will begin his ninth season coaching soccer at
Rockford College and his fifth as head coach of the women's program.
His soccer coaching experience has included coaching at many
levels of soccer, from Club youth programs to High School
Freshman, JV and Varsity women's programs to College men and
women programs. Coach Carley is assisted by Kristine Schaefer , a
former RC midfielder who is finishing up her degree with a major
in Physical Education and a minor in Education. She currently
holds the records for both goals and points in a career. A
graduate of Wartburg College (1964), Drake University (1996) and
the University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee (1976), Carley is a
Professor in the Department of Biology where he has been teaching
since 1966. <br>
<br>
</p>

