<TR>
<TD align="center"><IMG SRC="rcsign3.gif" HEIGHT=142 WIDTH=162></TD>

<TD align="center">
<H1>Women's Tennis<BR>
Rockford College</H1>
</TD>

<TD><IMG SRC="campus1.gif" HEIGHT=98 WIDTH=261></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><BR clear="left">
<A HREF="#The Program">The Program</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Steve Price, Head Coach">The Coach</A></P>

<P><A HREF="#Schedule Fall 96'">The Schedule</A></P>

<P><BR>
<BR>
</P>

<H2><A NAME="The Program"></A>The Program</H2>

<P>After a string of 4 consecutive NIIC Championships, the netters have
struggled with inconsistency on the roster and for a coach. Three different
coaches have led the Regents in the past four years, leading to a lack
of recruiting. With Coach Price and four returning players, the Regents
are hopeful of regaining the level of play they had enoyed a few years
ago. </P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

<H2><A NAME="Steve Price, Head Coach"></A>Steve Price, Head Coach</H2>

<P>Steve Price comes to the Regents in 1996 and takes on the challenge
of returning the Regents to the level at which they won the NIIC tournament
in 1993. Price played tennis at Illinois State University from 1965-69,
serving as team captain in both 1968 and 1969. He has given lessons in
the area for many years and won the 1995 Carter-Gates Coke Classic Open
Tennis Tournament in the 45 &amp; Over Singles and Doubles Championship.
He is also currently ranked 4th in the Northern Illinois Tennis Association
Men's 45 &amp; Over division. With the amount of experience and time to
recruit, Price is looking forward to staying with the program for some
time and returning it to past levels. </P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>

