<HTML>

<HEAD>
<Title>Rockford College News Media</title>
</head>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#251899" vlink="#870999">
<a NAME ="TOP"></a>

<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>
<p>August 28, 1996</p>
<h3>Rockford College students volunteer in their new community</h3>

p>For the third year in a row, Rockford College students, faculty and staff will pour into 
the Rockford community Friday, August 29, working at 10 sites for six local agencies in the 
annual "Rockford Plunge." Approximately 150 entering Rockford College students, returning 
students, faculty and staff will volunteer from 9:30 a.m. until 1:30 a.m.</p>
<p>"The Plunge is a way to introduce the students to the community and the community to our 
students," said Steve Marcon, Coordinator of Community Service. "A primary objective of our 
college is strengthening community ties.</p>
<p>"The end result of the Plunge is a win-win situation," he continued. "The recipient is a 
winner. The agency is a winner, and the volunteer is a winner."</p>
<p>The Plunge is an annual event that is part of "Starting Fresh," a week-long orientation 
program for new Rockford College students. Founded to promote an ethic of volunteerism in 
the Rockford College community, the Plunge gives new students a chance to meet faculty and 
other Rockford College students as they get to know the city of Rockford through community 
service.</p>
<p>This year, the students will serve in a variety of ways: they will clean up Aldeen Park 
(located directly behind the Rockford College campus), lay pavement bricks in a parking lot,  
set up for the "On The Waterfront" festival, and paint the interior of four houses on the west 
side of town, among other projects. </p>
<p>"If students learn the value of community service, it will help bring communities 
together," Marcon said. "College students are the next generation to help unite divided 
communities."</p>
<p>The Plunge will "kick-off" at 6:30 p.m. Thursday, August 29, in Grace Roper Lounge. 
Students will meet representatives from the agencies they are volunteering for. Rockford 
Park District, VIGOR, MELD, Rockford Neighborhood Redevelopment, Zion Development Corporation, 
and the Waterfront Committee will provide the Plunge sites for 1996. </p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad 
range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus 
masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves 
approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College 
is celebrating its Sesquicentennial in 1997.</p>
<p>#  #  #</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Office of College Relations at (815) 226-4140.</p>

