<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>

<p>August 5, 1996</p>
<h3 align="center">Registration underway at Rockford College Music Academy</h3>
<p>The Rockford  College Music Academy will begin registration for fall classes today and continue through Monday, September 2. </p>
<p>There are openings in the Music for the Young Child program for students six months to eight years old and in the traditional string and piano programs for students seven years old and older. </p>
<p>There also are openings in the Suzuki Talent Education program for both piano and strings for students three years old and up.</p>
<p>Scholarships are available for the classes, which begin in September. For more information or to register, contact the Rockford College Music Academy at (815) 226-4040. </p>
<p>The Rockford College Music Academy is a member of the National Guild of Community Schools of the Arts and is a not-for-profit community school of music designed to provide high-quality musical instruction regardless of age, ability to pay or demonstrated musical talent.</p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College is celebrating its Sesquicentennial in 1997.</p>
<p>#  #  #</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Office of College Relations at (815) 226-4140.</p>

