<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>

<p>August 6, 1996</p>
<h3 align="center">Two alumni participate in Rockford Art Museum exhibition</h3>
<p>Two Rockford College alumni are participating in the Rockford Art Museums 1996 Stateline Vicinity Exhibition, which opens at 6:30 p.m. Friday, August 23. The show is on display through October 6.</p>
<p>Cherri Rittenhouse earned a bachelor of fine arts degree from Rockford College in 1983, and Maggie Thienemann earned a bachelor of arts degree in 1953. Both women submitted slides for the juried biennial art show, which features artists from Rockford, Beloit, Chicago, Madison, Grand Rapids, Indianapolis and other cities throughout the Midwest. </p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College is celebrating its Sesquicentennial in 1997.</p>
<p>#  #  #</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Office of College Relations at (815) 226-4140.</p>

