<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>
<p>July 18, 1996</p>
<h3 align="center">Rockford College Golf Play Day held to support athletic programs</h3>
<p>The fifth annual Rockford College Golf Play Day will be held Monday, August 12, beginning at 9 a.m. at Aldeen Golf Club in Rockford. The Play Day supports Rockford College athletic programs and includes 18 holes of golf, cart, lunch and dinner, gifts, and a mini-clinic on the Aldeen practice course for $125.</p>
<p>Raffle prizes include two airline tickets to anywhere in the continental United States courtesy of American Airlines, a television and a Michael Jordan signature print. A silent auction of sports memorabilia and golf equipment will be held as well. An awards banquet will follow at 6 p.m. on the Rockford College campus.</p>
<p>Registration is required by August 5. For more information or to register individually or as a foursome, contact the Rockford College Athletic Department at (815) 226-4085.</p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College is celebrating its Sesquicentennial during the 1996-97 academic year.</p>
<p>#  #  #</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Office of College Relations at (815) 226-4140.</p>
