<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>


<p>July 15, 1996</p>
<h3 align="center">Director of Alumni Relations given additional responsibility</h3>
<p>Audra Freeze 91, Rockford College Director of Alumni Relations, has been given the additional responsibility of Parent Relations according to an announcement made today by John Gallagher, Vice President for Institutional Advancement. Freezes new title is Director of Alumni and Parent Relations.</p>
<p>The position was created to cultivate beneficial relationships with parents of future Rockford College alumni in addition to working with current alumni. </p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College is celebrating its Sesquicentennial during the 1996-97 academic year.</p>
