<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>

<p>July 29, 1996</p>
<h3 align="center">Rockford College names new Assistant Professor of Chemistry</h3>
<p>Dr. Deborah R. Breiter will join the Rockford College faculty as an Assistant Professor of Chemistry beginning in the Fall 1996 semester. </p>
<p>Breiter has a research interest in the structure and function of enzymes and has published several articles on the topic. From 1995 to 1996, Breiter was a visiting assistant professor of chemistry at Reed College in Portland, Ore.  </p>
<p>Breiter was awarded an Individual National Research Service Award in 1993 and a National Research Service Award in 1989, both from the National Institutes of Health.</p>
<p>Breiter received her Ph.D. in Physical Chemistry from the University of Wisconsin-Madison in 1991 and her bachelor of arts degree in chemistry and French from Grinnell College in Grinnell, Iowa, in 1987. She is a member of the American Chemical Society, the American Crystallographic Association and the Council on Undergraduate Research.</p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College is celebrating its Sesquicentennial in 1997.</p>
<p>#  #  #</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Office of College Relations at (815) 226-4140.</p>
<A HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/welcome.html">
