<BODY  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#251899" vlink="#870999">
<a NAME ="TOP"></a>

<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">News Release</h2>
<hr>
<h3>For immediate release</h3>
<p>July 22, 1996</p>
<h3 align="center">Rockford College begins construction on new entrance</h3>
<p>Construction begins Tuesday, July 23,  on the new main entrance and roadway configuration of the Rockford College campus. The cut-through road from the Turner Street entrance to the main State Street entrance will be closed, and traffic onto the campus from State Street may be affected by the construction, which is scheduled to be completed around Labor Day.</p>
<p>All Rockford College students and staff are requested to use the Turner Street entrance to the  campus and travel through the rear of the campus to reach buildings and parking areas.</p>
<p>The new State Street entrance will feature a brick and limestone pylon with three flagpoles. A new gateway with clock tower, also of brick and limestone, will be constructed at the beginning of the campus proper. An architects model of the project is on display in the lobby of Burpee Center. </p>
<p>This $500,000 project  which will include landscaping, new walkways and enhanced lighting   is funded by a gift to Rockford College from Larry Gloyd, a member and former chairman of the Rockford College Board of Trustees, and his wife Del.</p>
<p>Rockford College is a four-year independent coeducational institution offering a broad range of undergraduate degrees in traditional liberal arts and professional fields plus masters degrees in teaching and in business administration. Rockford College serves approximately 1,500 full- and part-time students. Chartered in 1847, Rockford College is celebrating its Sesquicentennial during the 1996-97 academic year.</p>
<p>#  #  #</p>
<p>For more information, contact the Office of College Relations at (815) 226-4140.</p>
</p>

