<html><Title>Rockford College Computing Society</Title>
<body background="backgrnd.gif"><center><B>
<h1>Rockford College Computing Society</h1></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="bartop.gif"></center>
<h2><center>Society Information</center></h2>
<p><p>The Rockford College Computing Society (RCCS) was founded in 1993. Its purpose is to give Society members a venue in which to pursue common and individual
interest in the field of Computer Science.<p>
<p>The Society has a  peer-to-peer network composed of five IBM-compatible computers. Other hardware includes a cd-rom drive, a color ink-jet printer, a scanner, and a  laser printer. <p>
<p>These services have been made available to everyone on campus, in order to provide them with enhanced computing capabilities. The Society provides laser and color printing, as well as scanning services.<p><p>
<P>
Anyone wishing to become a member of the Society, is welcome to send email to any Society Officer listed in the table below by simply clicking on their name.  Society meetings
are every other Monday night during the normal semester. 
<P><P>
<center>
<IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="computer.gif"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="colorptr.gif"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="scan.gif"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="cdrom.gif"><P></center>
