<P>
<HR width="100%"><FONT SIZE=+2><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">NEWS FEATURE:<BR>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#0000FF">&quot;A Better Man For A Better America!&quot;</FONT></FONT></P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.dole96.com"><IMG SRC="largebut.gif" ALT="College Republicans Support Bob Dole!" HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5 BORDER=2 HEIGHT=150 WIDTH=150 ALIGN=LEFT></A><FONT SIZE=+1>Bob
Dole believes in, &quot;more opportunities, smaller government, and stronger
and safer families.&quot; As U.S. senator for three decades, Bob Dole has
fought to protect America from forty years of Democratic oppression.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Bob Dole believes in economic freedom for American Families.
In relief from overly burdensome tax rates. In a balance national budget,
and in a debt free America. &quot;A Dole-Kemp administration will stop
reckess deficit spending once and for all for the good of this generation
and all generations which follow.&quot;</FONT></P>

<P><IMG SRC="dolepic.gif" HEIGHT=150 WIDTH=150 ALIGN=RIGHT><FONT SIZE=+1>The
Dole-Kemp team has a plan for restoring the economic growth rate from is
current low of 2.4 percent to 3.5 percent by the end of 1997. That will
put the American economy back where it was four years ago when Bill Clinton
sent it into a nose dive. Restoring the economic growth rate will set America
up for prosperity which will create jobs, low interest rates, and opportunity
for all Americans.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>&quot;My campaign is about telling the truth. It is about
what is right. It is about electing a president who is not attracted to
the glories of the office, but to its difficulties.&quot;</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Bob Dole - A better man for a better America!</FONT></P>
