<HTML>
<HEAD><BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">
<TITLE>Rockford College Academic Calendar - Fall 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

A <A HREF="/registr/cal/96f.htm">Netscape Enhanced</A>
version of this page is also available.


<h2>   ROCKFORD COLLEGE ACADEMIC CALENDAR - FALL 1996</h2>


<h3>August 23</h3>

Residence halls open for international students

<h3>August 25</h3>

Residence halls open for new students and returning Athletes (10 a.m.)<br>
Orientation for international students.

<h3>August 26-30</h3>

Freshman orientation program. (12 p.m.)

<h3>August 28</h3>

Pre-college Conference for faculty and staff. (9 a.m.)

<h3>August 30</h3>

Transfer student orientation program.<br>
Advising and registration for all new students.

<h3>September 1</h3>

Residence halls open for returning students.

<h3>September 2</h3>

LABOR DAY.  NO CLASSES.  OFFICES CLOSED.

<h3>September 3</h3>

CLASSES BEGIN.

<h3>September 5</h3>

Rockford College family picnic (employees and families). (5 p.m.)

<h3>September 11</h3>

President's Opening Convocation. (4 p.m.)

<h3>September 13</h3>

Last day to add courses. (4 p.m.)

<h3>September 20</h3>

Last day to drop courses without notation. (4 p.m.)<br>
Last day to file credit/audit forms.

<h3>October 11</h3>

Last day to file pass/fail forms. (4 p.m.)

<h3>October 14</h3>

OCTOBER DAYS.  NO CLASSES.  OFFICES CLOSED.

<h3>October 15</h3>

OCTOBER DAYS.  NO CLASSES.  Offices Open.

<h3>October 21-25</h3>

Mid-term exams.

<h3>October 25</h3>

Mid-term grades due in Registration Office. (4 p.m.)

<h3>November 4-15</h3>

Academic advising for spring semester pre-registration.

<h3>November 8</h3>

Last day to withdraw with "W". (4 p.m.)

<h3>November 18-22</h3>

Pre-registration for spring semester.

<h3>November 27-December 1</h3>

THANKSGIVING RECESS.  NO CLASSES.<br>
(Offices closed for Thanksgiving Recess on Thursday & Friday)  

<h3>December 2</h3>

CLASSES RESUME. (8 a.m.)

<h3>December 15</h3>

Recognition ceremony and reception for December graduates. (3 p.m.)

<h3>December 16</h3>

CLASSES END (10 p.m.)

<h3>December 17</h3>

Final exams for Tuesday evening classes.

<h3>December 18-21</h3>

Final exams. (<i>Monday evening final exams on Friday evening</i>)

<h3>December 23</h3>

All final grades due in Registration Office. (12 p.m.)<br>
Conflict exams (Grades due 9 a.m. Tuesday, December 24).<br>
Residence halls close. (7 p.m.)



<P>Final grades are due 48 hours after each exam, but no later
than 12 noon, Monday, December 23 for
regular exams.</P>


