<BODY>
<h1>DEPARTMENT OF MATHEMATICS</h1>
<HR>
<h2>FACULTY BACKGROUND</h2>
<HR>
<b>Dr. Gerald Caton -  Department Chair</b><HR><P></P>
Dr. Gerald Caton was born and raised in the Pacific Northwest.
He received his Bachelor of Arts Degree from Western Washington
State University, majoring in Mathematics and minoring in History.
He received a Master of Science Degree in Mathematics from Oregon 
State University and entered the Peace Corps, teaching at the University 
of the Philippines for two years, where he helped to establish the country's 
first computer research center.  He received his PhD. in Mathematics from the 
University of Montana. He has taught at Northern Montana State College, 
and came to Rockford College in 1979.  He helped to establish the 
Computer Science Department, and was among 60 mathematicians selected 
by the American Mathematical Society to attend the 15 month Institute for
Retraining in Computer Science.  He was chosen as the first recipient of 
Rockford College's Excellence in Teaching award, and he is presently 
serving as the Chair of the Computer Science & Math Departments.
<P>
<BR><HR>
<b>Mary Jeffreson Associate Professor</b><hr><P>
Associate Professor Mary Jeffreson joined Rockford College faculty in 1987 to teach both
computer science and mathematics.  She had previously lectured in mathematics in a 
South Australian teacher training college before migrating in the eighties 
and retraining in computer science.  She has taught most of the non-business oriented 
courses in the Computer Science major(which has undergone several revisions).
She is especially interested in artificial intelligence and its programming languages.  
She is planning a sabbatical in 1997-8 when she will undertake further 
Computer Science studies at a Chicago-area university.  
Her credentials are B.Sc., University of Sydney; B.A., University of 
New England, Australia; Adv. Dip.Ed, Adelaide, M.S.University of Nevada.
In July 1996 she informed Rockford College Computer Science alumnae 
and alumni that a Computer Science newsletter is planned, asking for 
news from them, either by e-mail or letter. If you are an alum 
who was not contacted and who has anything to tell us, please 
contact her by whatever medium you prefer.
<hr>
<b>Liang Jiao Huang, Ph.D.</b><HR><P></P>
Education:
....B.S. Xiamen University, China
....Ph.D., Michigan State University
Professional Experience:<BR>
....82-86: Numerical Analyst, the Reserach Institute of the Ministry of China(Chinas' NASA)<BR>
....86-92: Teaching Assistant, Michigan State University. <BR>
....92-Present: Assistant Professor of Mathematics, Rockford College<BR>
Presentations at Conferences:<BR>
....The 4th SIAM Conference on Linear Algebra and its Applications, 91<BR>
....The symposium on Matrix Analysis and Applications, 91<BR>
....The Annual AMS/MAA Joint Meeting, 92<BR>
....The 19th International COnference on Statistical Physics, 95<BR>
Publications in Journals:<BR>
.... Linear Algebra and Its Applications, 94<BR>
.... Journal of Computational and Applied Mathematics, 95<BR>
.... Journal of Mathematical Analysis and Applications, 96<BR>
Memberships in Professional Oranizations:<BR>
.... The Mathematical Association of America<BR>
.... Northern Illinois Association of Teachers of Mathematics<BR>
<p><BR>
<HR><P></P><A
HREF="mailto://gcaton@rockford.edu">...Request additional Department Information</A>
