<HEAD>
<TITLE>Accounting Detailed Course Descriptions</TITLE>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>Rockford College<BR>
Department of Accounting</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<H2>Detailed Course Descriptions</H2>
<HR>

<A NAME="223"></A>
<H3>223 Principles of Accounting I         4</H3>
<p> A comprehensive introduction to financial accounting for corporate and non-corporate
firms. Topics include basic accounting, merchandising, balance sheets, income statement,
statement of retained earnings, and statement of changes in financial position. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ:
Sophomore standing. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="224"></A>
<H3>224 Principles of Accounting II        4</H3>
<p>A completion of topics in financial accounting and a comprehensive introduction to
managerial accounting. Topics include cost-volume profit analysis, budgeting, decision-
making techniques, and methods of evaluating and controlling performance through
accounting systems.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 223. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="340"></A>
<H3>340 Intermediate Accounting Theory I   4</H3>
<p> The first third of a three-semester sequence. Topics include accounting theory and its
formation, inventory, and present-value techniques. There will be an in-depth analysis
of current and long-term assets and liabilities. Appropriate professional literature will
be integrated in such discussions.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 224. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="341"></A>
<H3>341 Intermediate Accounting Theory II  4</H3>
<p>The second third of a three-semester sequence. Topics include stockholders equity,
earnings per share calculations, investments, and the statement of cash flows. Revenue
recognition, accounting changes, income tax allocation, pensions, and leases are all
discussed in depth. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 340. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="342"></A>
<H3>342 Intermediate Accounting Theory III 4</H3>
<p>The final course of a three-semester sequence, the most important financial accounting
tract for accounting majors. This course will complete the financial accounting topics,
including leases, statement of cash flows, accounting changes, and financial statement
analysis. The course will "cap off" with various advanced level issues to be solved using
a computerized spreadsheet approach.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 340, 341. May be taken concurrently with
Acct 444,445,446 and/or 495. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Fall semester only.
</A>

<A NAME="344"></A>
<H3>344 Cost Accounting               4</H3>
<p>Comprehensive coverage of cost accounting. Topics include cost-volume-profit analysis,
process costing, job-order costing, budgeting techniques, and methods of motivation.
Standard costs, flexible budgeting, and absorption costing will all be discussed along with
relevant costs and capital budgeting.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 224. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="345"></A>
<H3>345 Federal Taxes                 4</H3>
<p> A comprehensive introduction to the U.S. federal tax system with emphasis on individual
income taxes. Topics include gross income determination, business deductions, and non-
business deductions. Special computations and credits will be discussed along with
ordinary gains and losses and capital gains and losses.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 224. Meets: NO.
Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="398"></A>
<H3>398 Accounting Internship              1-4</H3>
<p><A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Junior standing and consent. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="399"></A>
<H3>399 Accounting Internship              1-4</H3>
<p><A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Junior standing and consent. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="444"></A>
<H3>444 Advanced Cost Accounting      4</H3>
<p>An in-depth analysis of special topics in cost accounting. A variety of advanced methods
for the use of managerial accounting information will be presented with the mathematical
methods necessary for their use.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 344 and Math 223 or 224. Meets: NO. Scheduled:
Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="445"></A>
<H3>445 Advanced Federal Taxes        4</H3>
<p>An in-depth study of tax situations in partnerships, estates, trusts, and corporations.
Emphasis will be on special tax problems for business, along with estate and gift taxes.
<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 224, 345. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="446"></A>
<H3>446 Advanced Accounting           4</H3>
<p>An advanced course in accounting theories and practices. Topics include partnership
accounting, estates and trusts, international operations, and governmental accounting.
The major emphasis will be placed on consolidated financial statement theory and
preparations, including the areas of acquisition and intercompany transactions.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct
341. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="447"></A>
<H3>447 Auditing Theory and Practice  4</H3>
<p>A comprehensive presentation of the theory and practice involved in the auditing process.
The environment of auditing will be presented, including the AICPA professional standards.
The methods of verifying accounting records will be discussed, along with sampling
techniques, EDP auditing, and the auditors report. The use of professional literature and
practical examples will aid the development of the practices involved.
<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Acct 341 and
Math 223 or 224. Meets: NO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="495"></A>
<H3>495 Senior Seminar                4</H3>
<p><A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Senior standing, consent. Meets: N. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.
</A>

<A NAME="498"></A>
<H3>498 Accounting Internship              1-4</H3>
<p><A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Senior standing, consent. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.
</A>

<A NAME="499"></A>
<H3>499 Accounting Internship              1-4</H3>
<p><A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Senior standing, consent. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.
</A>


<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/welcome.html">
Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</A>
<HR>



