<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE>Art Detailed Course Descriptions</TITLE>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>Rockford College <BR>
Department of Art</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<H2>Detailed Course Descriptions</H2>
<HR>

<PRE>
<A NAME="105"></A>
<H3>105 Beginning Drawing - 2 hours</H3>
Drawing defined as a response to perceptual understanding; emphasis on developing eye-hand
coordination, understanding light as it applies to illusion of structure, and an introduction to
composition. PRQ: None. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly. 

<A NAME="107"></A>
<H3>107 Beginning Painting - 2 hours</H3>
An introductory course in the paint medium building on the foundation developed in drawing.
Various properties of paint and techniques of application will be explored, as well as further
emphasis on composition.  PRQ: Art 105 or consent of instructor.  Classified: B.  Meets: ANO. 
Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="109"></A>
<H3>109 Basic Design (2-D) - 2 hours</H3>
An introduction to two-dimensional design stressing the formal analysis of lines and shapes on a
flat plane, color theory, organizational systems, space and perspective, representation of values
and texture as they apply to the flat surface. PRQ: None. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled:
Fall, yearly.

<A NAME="110"></A>
<H3>110 Basic Design (3-D) - 2 hours</H3> 
An introduction to three-dimensional design stressing the formal analysis of lines and shapes in
space, organizational systems, additive and reductive construction methods, color and texture as
elements in the round. PRQ: None. Classified: B.  Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. 

<A NAME="113"></A>
<H3>113 Beginning Ceramics - 2 hours</H3> 
An introduction to creating art using the ceramic process. The nature of clay and the firing
process will be combine with units on hand-building, throwing on the wheel, methods of
decoration and glazing and the development of a personal aesthetic. PRQ: None. Classified: B.
Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly. 

<A NAME="115"></A>
<H3>115 Beginning Sculpture - 2 hours</H3>
Introduction to sculpture through modeling and casting.  Perceptual skills will be combined with
the development of a sculptural aesthetic through a variety of exercises. PRQ: None. Classified:
B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="117"></A>
<H3>117 Beginning Intaglio - 2 hours</H3>
An introduction to the graphic arts and producing multiple images through Intaglio printing. All
the basic Intaglio processes will be covered with an emphasis on developing an understanding of
etching as a unique and expressive artistic medium. PRQ: None. Classified: B. Meets: ANO.
Scheduled: Every three semesters.

<A NAME="123"></A>
<H3>123 Beginning Lithography - 2 hours</H3>
An introduction to stone lithography with emphasis on its inherently involved technical
procedures while continuing to develop craftsmanship, discipline, and personal imagery. PRQ:
Art 105 or consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Every three semesters.

<A NAME="125"></A>
<H3>125 Beginning Relief Printing - 2 hours</H3>
An introduction to printmaking by making images from the relief surfaces of found objects,
wood and linoleum blocks, and collages to explore the impact upon seeing by composing with
whole shapes. PRQ: None. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Every three semesters.

<A NAME="127"></A>
<H3>127 Beginning Photography - 2 hours</H3>
(XL:Com 127) An introduction to black-and-white photography that emphasizes personal forms
of visual communication and image making rather than passive picture taking. Students will
create handmade photographs by direct manipulation of light-sensitive materials, and they will
make their own cameras before progressing to the use of 35mm cameras. 35mm camera required.
PRQ: None. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: On request.

<A NAME="205"></A>
<H3>205 Intermediate Drawing - 3 hours</H3>
Continued development of drawing skills with an emphasis on compositional uses of
representational subject matter.  Developing a personal aesthetic is also covered. PRQ: Art 105
or consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="207"></A>
<H3>207 Intermediate Painting - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="307"></A>
<H3>307 Advanced Painting I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="407"></A>
<H3>407 Advanced Painting II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration in various paint media with emphasis on development of an intellectual basis
for personal imagery, sound conceptual and technical skills, good work habits, creative
independent thinking and self-discipline. Projects developed in consultation with the instructor to
suit the students needs and desires.  PRQ: Art 107 for 207, all others in order; or consent of
instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="210"></A>
<H3>210 Archaeology of the Ancient World - 3 hours</H3>
(XL: Classics 210) A study of the monuments and other material remains that illustrate the
historical development of Greece and Rome. Some attention will be paid to the topography of
Athens and Rome and of other selected sites. Guest lecturers, such as those of the Archaeological
Institute of America, may present information in related areas, e.g., on the Egyptians,
Phoenicians, etc. Some major archaeologists will be discussed for their contributions.
Non-studio. PRQ: None. Meets: ALNOS. Scheduled: Alternate years.

<A NAME="213"></A>
<H3>213 Intermediate Ceramics - 3 hours</H3>
A continuation of 113, with emphasis on individual exploration and more advanced techniques
and ideas. PRQ: Art 113 or consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring,
yearly.

<A NAME="215"></A>
<H3>215 Intermediate Sculpture - 3 hours</H3>
Further introductory work in sculpture using construction and carving. Students are directed
toward a personal sculptural vocabulary and more emphasis is placed on the abstract formal
qualities of sculpture. PRQ: Art 115. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.

<A NAME="217"></A>
<H3>217 Intermediate Intaglio - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="317"></A>
<H3>317 Advanced Intaglio I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="417"></A>
<H3>417 Advanced Intaglio II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration in Intaglio printing processes, including paper-making. PRQ: Art 117 for
217, all others in order, or consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring,
yearly.

<A NAME="223"></A>
<H3>223 Intermediate Lithography - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="323"></A>
<H3>323 Advanced Lithography I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="423"></A>
<H3>423 Advanced Lithography II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration in lithographic processes. PRQ: Art 123 for 223, all others in order, or
consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Yearly.

<A NAME="225"></A>
<H3>225 Intermediate Relief Printing - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="325"></A>
<H3>325 Advanced Relief Printing I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="425"></A>
<H3>425 Advanced Relief Printing II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration in relief printing processes. PRQ: Art 125 for 225, all others in order, or
consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Yearly.

<A NAME="227"></A>
<H3>227 Intermediate Photography - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="327"></A>
<H3>327 Advanced Photography I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="427"></A>
<H3>427 Advanced Photography II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration of photographic processes and concepts. PRQ: Art 127 for 227, all others in
order, or consent of instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.

<A NAME="245"></A>
<H3>245 Survey of Western Art I - 3 hours</H3>
Survey of the history of Western Art from the prehistoric period to 1400 A.D., the end of the
Gothic era. Architecture, sculpture, painting and the decorative arts will be considered. PRQ:
None. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.

<A NAME="246"></A>
<H3>246 Survey of Western Art II - 3 hours</H3>
Survey of the history of Western Art from the Early Italian Renaissance, 1300 A.D. to the
present. Architecture, sculpture, painting, printmaking and photography will be considered. PRQ:
None. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="300"></A>
<H3>300 Independent Studio Seminar - 3 hours</H3>
A studio course fostering self-determination of ideas and directions for continued development in
the students area of concentration. Develop the student's potential to work independently of
assignments and class structure. Students from various disciplines meet weekly to discuss and
critique work. PRQ: At least two courses in area of studio concentration. Classified: B. Meets:
ANO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.

<A NAME="305"></A>
<H3>305 Advanced Drawing I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="405"></A>
<H3>405 Advanced Drawing II - 3 hours</H3>
The use of drawing to create art with emphasis on personal expression, creative exploration and
mastery of a variety of drawing media. Students will seek growth and refinement at each level as
they pursue a high level of artistic competence. PRQ: Art 205 for 305, 305 for 405; or consent of
instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.

<A NAME="313"></A>
<H3>313 Advanced Ceramics I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="413"></A>
<H3>413 Advanced Ceramics II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration in the ceramic medium with emphasis on developing an intellectual basis for
personal imagery, sound conceptual and technical skills, good work habits, creative independent
thinking and self-discipline. Projects will be developed in consultation with the instructor to meet
the needs and desires of the student. PRQ: Art 213 for 313, 313 for 413; or consent of instructor.
Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="315"></A>
<H3>315 Advanced Sculpture I - 3 hours</H3>

<A NAME="415"></A>
<H3>415 Advanced Sculpture II - 3 hours</H3>
Further exploration of various sculpture techniques with personal imagery, sound conceptual and
technical skills, good work habits, creative independent thinking and self-discipline. Additive
and subtractive processes will be considered. PRQ: Art 215 for 315, 315 for 415; or consent of
instructor. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.

<A NAME="330"></A>
<H3>330 Art History Methodology - 3 hours</H3>
An introduction to the study of the history of art, treating areas of investigation, problems of the
discipline, i.e., dating, attributions, stylistic analysis, etc., and writing research papers and
catalogs. PRQ: Art 245, 246, art history majors only. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: On request.

<A NAME="346"></A>
<H3>346 Medieval Art - 3 hours</H3>
The history of medieval art from the Age of Constantine (300 A.D.) to 1500 A.D. The materials
treated will include architecture, sculpture, painting and the portable arts within the historical
context of the time. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245, 246 or consent of instructor. Meets: ANO.
Scheduled: Every two years.

<A NAME="347"></A>
<H3>347 Italian Renaissance - 3 hours</H3>
A survey of the art history of Italy from 1300 A.D. to 1525 A.D.  Painting, sculpture and
architecture will be examined. The ideas and contributions of Renaissance artists will be treated
in historical context. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245 and 246, or consent of instructor. Meets:
ANO. Scheduled: Every two years.

<A NAME="348"></A>
<H3>348 Northern Renaissance - 3 hours</H3>
A survey of the art history of Northern Europe from the International Style, circa 1400 A.D., to
the death of Breughel, 1569 A.D. The emphasis is on painting, with sculpture and architecture
also treated. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245 and 246, or consent of instructor. Meets: ANO.
Scheduled: Every two years.

<A NAME="349"></A>
<H3>349 Baroque and Rococo Art - 3 hours</H3>
A study of developments in art history during the 16th, 17th, and 18th centuries in European
architecture, sculpture and painting. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245 and 246, or consent of
instructor. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Every two years.

<A NAME="351"></A>
<H3>351 19th Century Art - 3 hours</H3>
Developments of European art from the end of the 18th century (the French Revolution) to the
turn of the 20th century, circa 1900.  Architecture, sculpture and painting will be presented in
historical context. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245 and 246, or consent of instructor. Meets: ANO.
Scheduled: Every two years.

<A NAME="352"></A>
<H3>352 Early 20th Century Art - 3 hours</H3>
An examination of changes in architecture, sculpture and painting from the Symbolists and Art
Nouveau to the end of World War II, 1945. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245 and 246, or consent of
instructor. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: Every two years.

<A NAME="355"></A>
<H3>355 Late 20th Century Art - 3 hours</H3>
Trends in art from 1945 to the present. PRQ: Junior standing, Art 245 and 246, or consent of
instructor. Meets: ANO. Scheduled: On request. 

<A NAME="360"></A>
<H3>360 The Art and Architecture of Britain - 3 hours</H3>
To be offered only at Regent's College.

<A NAME="400"></A>
<H3>400 Contemporary Issues - 3 hours</H3>
A studio course bringing together students from the various areas of concentration to emphasize
that ideas are the common bond between artists. Students will direct their medium to the issues
and concepts in contemporary art introduced during weekly discussions and critiques.  PRQ: At
least three courses in area of studio concentration. Classified: B. Meets: ANO. Scheduled:
Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="494"></A>
<H3>494 Senior Project - 3 hours</H3>
Independent guided research or creative work in the students chosen area of concentration. PRQ:
Senior art majors. Meets: N. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.

<A NAME="495"></A>
<H3>495 Senior Seminar - 3 hours</H3>
An examination of the formal problems and aesthetic theories confronting the visual artist in the
20th century, taught partially within the context of the students work. PRQ: Senior art majors.
Meets: N. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.
</PRE>

