<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT23-B01-95</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA016-000171-B004-283</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.rockford.edu:80/orgs/crepub/crcons.htm 192.217.12.8 19970105235807 text/html 8733
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Sun, 05 Jan 1997 23:41:38 GMT
Server: NCSA/1.4.2
Content-type: text/html
Last-modified: Thu, 17 Oct 1996 21:53:35 GMT
Content-length: 8557
</DOCHDR>
<html>

<BODY>

      <center><H1>Rockford College Republican Club</H1></center><P>
      <P>
      <center><H2>Constitution</H2></center><P>
      <P>
      <center><H3>Article I: Name</H3></center><P>
      <P>
      The name of this organization shall be the Rockford College Republican Club.<P>
      <P>
      <center><H3>Article II:  Purposes</H3></center><P>
      <P>
      <UL>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 1</STRONG>:  To make know and promote the principles of the Republican Party among the students at Rockford College.<p>
         <p>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 2</STRONG>:  To provide access to membership procedures for the Republican Party<p>
         <p>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 3</STRONG>:  To offer members a chance to aid in the election of Republican candidates at all levels of government.<p>
         <p>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 4</STRONG>:  To develop politicskills and leadership abilities among the members.<p>
      </UL>
      <center><H3>Article III: Membership and Voting</H3></center><p>
      <p>
      <UL>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 1</STRONG>:  Membership shall be open to all stuednts meeting the Rockford College Student Government membership requirements.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 2</STRONG>:  Members shall have the right to vote after attending two meetings.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 3</STRONG>:  Members of the Rockford College Republican Club shall be offered the opportunity to join the nation organization of College Republicans by filling out the College Republicans Membership form.<P>
         <p>
      </ul>
      <center><H3>Article IV:  Officers</H3></center><p>
      <P>
      <UL>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 1</STRONG>:  The officers shall be a chairman, first vice-chairman, second vice-chariman, secretary, and treasurer.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 2</STRONG>:  The officers shall be elected at a regular meeting between March 1 and April 20 and shall take office immediately opon election.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 3</STRONG>:  Notice that the election of the officers will occur at the regular meeting must be resonably provided to all members not less than two weeks prior to such meeting.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 4</STRONG>:  Nominations of candidates for officer positions shall be made from the floor by andy member.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 5</STRONG>:  Officers shallbe elected by a majority of those eligible woting members present.  No proxy boting shall be permitted.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 6</STRONG>:  Vacancies occurring among the officers shall be filled at the next regular meeting after such vacancy occurs, provided however, that upon a vacancy in the position of chairman, the first vice-chairman shall become chairman, and opon a vacancy in the position of first vice-chairman, the second vice-chairman shall become the first vice-chairman.<P>
         <P>
         <L1><STRONG>Section 7</STRONG>:  The duties of the officers shall be as follows:<P>
         <P>
         <UL>
            <LI><STRONG> Chariman</STRONG> - To preside over all meeting of the Rockford College Republican Club and all meetings of the officers; to represent the club in an official capacity; to send updated leadership changes to the College Republican National Committee; and to plan the activities for the club.<P>
            <P>
            <LI><STRONG>First Vice-Chariman</STRONG> - To preside in the absence of the Chariman; to coordinate campaign activities; to perform such other tasks as the chariman may assign.<P>
            <P>
            <LI><STRONG>Second Vice-Chairman</STRONG> - To preside in the absence of the Chairman and the First Vice-Chariman; to coordinate recruitment activities; to perform such other tasks as the chariman may assign.<P>
            <P>
            <LI><STRONG>Secretary</STRONG> - To prepare the minutes of all regular meetings; to send official correspondences; to coordinate preparation and distribution of publications.<P>
            <P>
            <LI><STRONG>Treasurer</STRONG> - To make financial reports at all regular meetings; to receive and distribute funds upon authorization by the Chairmanl to coordinate fund raising activities; and ensure compliance with any governmental laws or regulations governing club finances.<P>
            <P>
         </UL>
      </UL>
      <center><h3>Article V:  Appointive Positions</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      The chairman shall appoint, with the consent of a majority of the officers, such project directors, committee chairmen, committees, residence hass, and commuter coordinators as may contribute to the successful operation of the Rockford College Republican Club.<p>
      <p>
      <center><h3>Article VI:  Regular Meetings</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      <ul>
         <l1><strong>Section 1</strong>:  The Rockford College Republican Club shall hold regular meetings not less than once monthly while school is in session.<p>
         <p>
         <l1><strong>Section 2</strong>:  Regular meetings may be held at the call of the chairman or of any three officers, or upon the written and signed request of ten club members, or by majority of a regular meeting present at a duly called meeting.  Notice of a regular meeting shall 
            be given to all members in the most complete manner practivable not less than one week prior to the meeting.<p>
         <p>
      </ul>
      <center><h3>Article VII:  Advisor</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      The Rockford College Republican Club shall have an advisor who is a member of the faculty or administration at Rockford College as stated in the Rockford College Student Government Constitution.  He or shi shall be kept informed of all matters pertaining to the organization.<p>
      <p>
      <center><h3>Article VIII: Recruitment</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      <ul>
         <l1><strong>Section 1</strong>:  A membership table shall be run during the Rockford College Club Fair in order to recruit new members.<p>
         <p>
         <l1><strong>Section 2</strong>:  The first regular meeting shall be held not more than three days after the membership table is run.<p>
      </ul>
      <p>
      <center><h3>Article IX:  Impeachment</h3></center>
      <p>
      Any officer my be impeached for failure to perform his/her prescribed duties properly and in good faith after being notified abouut the impeachment in writing at least one week prior o the meeting at which the impeachement will be considered.  Any candidate for impeachment shall be given
         an opportunity to address the club prior to a vote.  Upon a two thirds vote of eligible voting members present, an officer shall be removed from his/her position.  The position shall remain vacant until the next regular meeting when an election to fill the vacancy shall be held.  Any member 
         may seek election to fill the vacancy.  The removed officer may not seek election as an officer until the next semester after the impeachment.<p>
      <p>
      <center><h3>Article X:  Amendments</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      Ammendments to this constitution may be adopted upon an affirmative vote by two-thirds (2/3) of those present at two successive regular meetings, provided however that no such ammendments shall take effect without the approval of at least three officers.  Amendments may be proposed ay any regular meeting.
         The secretary will type the proposed amendment and distribute it at the next regular meeting.  The chairman will allow time for discussion and then call for a vote.  No ammendment can be voted on at the same meeting that it was proposed.<p>
      <p>
      <center><h3>Article XI:  Parlimentary Authority</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      The most recent edition of Robert's Rules of Order, Newly Revised shall govern the Club in all circumstances not dealt with by thie rules, procedures, and policies outlined in this constitution.<p>
      <p>
      <center><h3>Ratification and Effective Date</h3></center><p>
      <p>
      This consitution shall become effective as of April 25, 1995, upon two thirds affirmative vote of eligible voting members, and a copy shall be kept as the official chartering record of this organization at the National Headquarters of the College Republican National Committee in Washington, DC.</ul><p>
   </body>
</html>



</DOC>
