<html>

<head>
<title>Learning Disabilities Course Offerings and
Descriptions
</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<base href="http://www.rockford.edu">
</head>

<body>
<h1 align=center>Learning Disabilities Course Offerings and
Descriptions</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Detailed Course Descriptions</h2>
<hr>
<a name="200a&b"></a><h3>LD 200A&B Field Experience: LD I       1</h3></a>
<p>To pursue qualification as a learning disabilities specialist, the student must complete
supervised field experience before the LD teaching semester.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: None. Classified: C.
Meets: N. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.
</a></p>
<a name="201a&b"></a><h3>LD 201A&B Field Experience: LD II      1</h3></a>
<p>Supervised LD field experience during the LD teaching semester.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: LD 200. Classified: C.
Meets: N. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.</a> </p>
<a name="342"></a><h3>342 Development and Education of Exceptional Children                  3</h3></a>
<p>Survey of exceptional children and educational adaptations: giftedness, retardation, visual,
auditory and orthopedic handicaps, speech disorders, learning disabilities, cultural
deprivations, social/emotional problems.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: None. Meets: N. Scheduled: Fall, spring and
summer, yearly.
</a> </p>
<a name="408"></a><h3>408 Student Teaching in Elementary School   5</h3></a>
<p>Classroom observation, assistance to the teacher, and actual teaching supervised by the
classroom teacher and the college supervisor. Fee: $100.00.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Enrollment in teaching
semester. Classified: C. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.</a> </p>
<a name="409"></a><h3>409 Student Teaching in Secondary School    5</h3></a>
<p>Classroom observation, assistance to the teacher, and actual teaching supervised by the
classroom teacher and the college supervisor. Fee: $100.00.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Enrollment in teaching
semester. Classified: C. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.</a></p>
<a name="458"></a><h3>458 Learning Disabilities: Characteristics  3</h3></a>
<p>A study of the abilities and disabilities of children with specific difficulties in learning,
with emphasis on distinguishing learning abilities from general mental impairment and from
emotional and motivational interference with learning.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: LD 342. Meets: N. Scheduled: Fall,
yearly.</a> </p>
<a name="460"></a><h3>460 LD/BD/MI (EMH/TMH): Diagnosis      3</h3></a>
<p>Differential diagnosis of learning disabilities, mental impairment, and behavioral disorders.
Selecting and administering tests of abilities and school achievement; types of test scores
and use of data on validity, reliability, intercorrelation, and factor analysis; interpretation
of data patterns from tests, observations, and history.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: LD 458. Meets: N. Scheduled:
Spring, yearly; even second summer.
</a></p>
<a name="462"></a><h3>462 Learning Disability: Methods            3</h3></a>
<p>Offers a practical application of methods, techniques, and materials for teaching children
with learning disabilities; principles underlying prescriptive programming, behavior
modification, and materials both commercial and self-made are emphasized.
<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: LD 458.
Meets: N. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.
</a> </p>
