<body>
<h1 align=center>Rockford College<br>
Department of Modern Languages</h1>
<hr>
<h2>French Course Offerings and Descriptions</h2>
<hr>
<A NAME="f101"></A>
<h3>101 Elementary French I 4</h3>
Pronunciation, conversational skills, cultural readings and basic grammar. Laboratory work 
required. Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: None. Meets: F. Scheduled: Fall, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="f102"></A>
<h3>102 Elementary French II 4 </h3>
Pronunciation, conversational skills, cultural readings and basic grammar. Laboratory work 
required. Conducted in French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 101 or equivalent, placement exam or consent. 
Meets: F. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</a> </p>
<A NAME="f203"></A>
<h3>203 Intermediate French 4 </h3>
<p>Review of grammar; development of oral and writing proficiency. Laboratory work required. 
Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 102 or equivalent, placement exam or consent. Meets: FNO. 
Scheduled: Fall, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="f207"></A>
<h3>207 Intermediate French Conversation 2 </h3>
<p>Continued practice and development of oral ability through oral presentations and discussions of readings from contemporary cultural materials. The emphasis is on practical vocabulary and idiomatic usage. Conducted in French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 203 or equivalent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: 
Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="f208"></A>
<h3>208 Intermediate French Composition 2 </h3>
<p>Further acquisition of vocabulary and increased control of grammar in written French. Conducted in 
French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 203 or equivalent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="f301"></A>
<h3>301 Survey of French Literature I 3 </h3>
<p>Selected readings from the Middle Ages through the 18th century. Conducted in French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: 
French 203 or equivalent, placement exam or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="f302"></A>
<h3>302 Survey of French Literature II 3 </h3>
<p>Selected readings from the 19th and 20th centuries. Conducted in French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 203 or 
equivalent, placement exam or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="f303"></A>
<h3>303 Advanced Conversation 2 </h3>
<p>Conversation, oral reports, debates and discussions on selected topics. Conducted in French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: 
French 207 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="f304"></A>
<h3>304 Advanced Composition 2 </h3>
<p>Practice in &quot;theme&quot; and free compositions to develop greater flexibility and precision in writing. 
Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 208 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request.</a> </p>
<A NAME="f308"></A>
<h3>308 French Culture and Civilization 3 </h3>
<p>A study of the historical, social, political and artistic institutions of France. Conducted in French. 
<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: French 203 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="f318"></A>
<h3>318 French Novel 3</h3>
<p>A study of representative masterpieces of the novel in France. Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: One 
300-level course or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="f319"></A>
<h3>319 French Theatre 3</h3>
<p>A study of representative masterpieces of the theatre in France. Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: One 
300-level course or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request.</a> </p>
<A NAME="f320"></A>
<h3>320 French Poetry 3</h3>
<p>A study of representative masterpieces of poetry in France. Conducted in French. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: One 300 
level course or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="f379"></A>
<h3>379 Selected Topics in French Culture and Civilization 3</h3>
<p>In-depth cultural study selected from Women's Voices, Voices of Humor and Fantasy, Voices of the French-Speaking World, and Voices of the French Language from Roman times to the Present. Discussions will be based on representative readings. Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Fren 203 or 
consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request.</a></p>
<A NAME="f495"></A>
<h3>495 Senior Seminar 4 </h3>
<p>Conducted in French.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Sr. Meets: N. Scheduled: On request.</a></p>
<HR>
<h2>German Course Offerings and Descriptions</h2>
<hr>
<A NAME="g101"></A>
<h3>101 Elementary German I 4 </h3>
<p>Pronunciation, conversational skills, cultural readings, and basic grammar. Laboratory work 
required. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: None. Meets: F. Scheduled: Fall, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="g102"></A>
<h3>102 Elementary German II 4 </h3>
<p>Pronunciation, conversational skills, cultural readings and basic grammar. Laboratory work 
required. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 101. Meets: F. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</a> </p>
<A NAME="g203"></A>
<h3>203 Intermediate German 4 </h3>
<p>Review of grammar; development of basic proficiency in written and spoken German. Laboratory work required. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 102 or equivalent, placement exam or 
consent. Meets: FNO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="g207"></A>
<h3>207 German Conversation 2 </h3>
<p>Development of oral ability in German through drills, presentations, and discussions of readings based upon contemporary topics. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 203. Meets: LNO. 
Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="g208"></A>
<h3>208 Intermediate Composition 2 </h3>
<p>Practice in writing and reading German with emphasis on the structure of the language. Course work involves translations, written exercises, discussions of syntactical problems, and compositions based on literary, scientific, and cultural readings. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 203. 
Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="g301"></A>
<h3>301 Survey of French Literature I 3 </h3>
<p>Study of the most representative writers and the major literary movements of German literature from 800 to 1750. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 207, 208 or equivalent, placement exam or 
consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="g302"></A>
<h3>302 Survey German Literature II 3 </h3>
<p>Study of the most representative writers and the major literary movements of German literature from 
1750 to present. Conducted in German.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 207, 208 or equivalent, placement exam or 
consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="g303"></A>
<h3>303 Advanced Conversation and Composition I 3 </h3>
<p>Development of oral and written communication in German based on contemporary and vocational topics. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 207, 208 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="g304"></A>
<h3>304 Advanced Conversation and Composition II 3 </h3>
<p>Development of oral and written communication in German based upon cultural and historical topics. Conducted in German.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: German 207, 208 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request.</a> </p>
<A NAME="g310"></A>
<h3>310 German Poetry 3 </h3>
<p>A chronological examination of the most important German poets from the Middle Ages to the present. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: One 300-level course or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="g312"></A>
<h3>312 German Novel 3 </h3>
<p>Study of representative writers. The works selected will vary. Conducted in German.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: One 300-level course or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="g314"></A>
<h3>314 German Drama 3 </h3>
<p>Study of representative dramatists. The dramas selected will vary. Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: One 300 level course or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request.</a> </p>
<A NAME="g495"></A>
<h3>495 Senior Seminar 4 </h3>
<p>Conducted in German. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Sr. Meets: N. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<hr>
<h2>Spanish Course Offerings and Descriptions</h2>
<hr>
<A NAME="s101"></A>
<h3>101 Elementary Spanish I 4 </h3>
<p>Pronunciation, conversational skills, cultural readings and basic grammar. Laboratory work required. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: None. Meets: F. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="s102"></A>
<h3>102 Elementary Spanish II 4 </h3>
<p>Pronunciation, conversational skills, cultural readings, and basic grammar. Laboratory work required. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 101. Meets: F. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.</a> </p>
<A NAME="s203"></A>
<h3>203 Intermediate Spanish 4 </h3>
<p>Review of grammar; development of oral and writing proficiency. Cultural readings. Laboratory work required. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 102 or equivalent, placement exam or 
consent. Meets: FNO. Scheduled: Fall and spring, yearly.</a> </p>
<A NAME="s207"></A>
<h3>207 Intermediate Spanish Conversation 2 </h3>
<p>Development of conversational skills. Laboratory work required. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 203. Meets LNO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="s208"></A>
<h3>208 Intermediate Spanish Composition 2 </h3>
<p>Development of composition skills. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 203. Classified: 1Y. 
Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<A NAME="s301"></A>
<h3>301 Survey of Spanish Literature I 3 </h3>
<p>Study of literary movements in Spain from the Middle Ages to mid-19th Century, with selected readings. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 203, equivalent, placement exam or consent. Meets: 
LNO. Scheduled: Fall, odd years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s302"></A>
<h3>302 Survey of Spanish Literature II 3 </h3>
<p>Study of literary movements in Spain from the mid-19th Century to the present, with selected readings. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 203, equivalent, placement exam or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Spring, even years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s303"></A>
<h3>303 Advanced Conversation I 3 </h3>
<p>Development of oral ability in Spanish with readings and discussion based on Spanish-American cultural themes. Laboratory work is required. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 207 or consent. Meets: LNOR. Scheduled: Fall, odd years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s304"></A>
<h3>304 Advanced Composition I 3 </h3>
<p>Development in advanced composition skills with discussion and readings based on Latino cultural themes. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 208 or consent. Meets: LNOR.Scheduled: Spring, 
even years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s305"></A>
<h3>305 Advanced Conversation II 3 </h3>
<p>Development of oral ability in Spanish and of a practical vocabulary designed for the students'  vocational interests. Laboratory work required. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 207 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Fall, even years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s306"></A>
<h3>306 Advanced Composition II 3 </h3>
<p>Development of advanced composition skills, with discussions and readings based on Spanish cultural themes. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 208 or consent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Spring, odd years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s309"></A>
<h3>309 History of Spanish Language and Phonetics 3 </h3>
<p>Introduction to the phonetics and phonology, both descriptive and historical, of the Spanish language. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 207 or 208. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Fall, even years.</a> </p>
<A NAME="s320"></A>
<h3>320 Golden Age Drama and Poetry 3 </h3>
<p>A study of the drama and poetry of the 16th and 17th centuries in Spain. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 301. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="s321"></A>
<h3>321 Golden Age of Prose/Cervantes 3 </h3>
<p>A study of Don Quijote De La Mancha and of Golden Age prose. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 301. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="s323"></A>
<h3>323 Contemporary Spanish Literature I 3 </h3>
<p>Spanish literature from mid-19th Century through the early 20th Century. Conducted in 
Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 302. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="s324"></A>
<h3>324 Contemporary Spanish Literature II 3 </h3>
<p>A study of Spanish literature from about 1936 to the present. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 302. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: On request. </a></p>
<A NAME="s330"></A>
<h3>330 Survey of Spanish-American Literature 3 </h3>
<p>The principal literary movements in Spanish-America from the beginning to the present. Conducted in Spanish.<a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 203, equivalent, placement exam or consent. Meets: LNOR. Scheduled: Spring, odd years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s331"></A>
<h3>331 Spanish-American Theatre 3 </h3>
<p>The theatre in Spanish-America in the 20th century. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 301, 302, 330 or consent. Meets: LNOR. Scheduled: Fall, even years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s332"></A>
<h3>332 Spanish-American Short Story 3 </h3>
<p>The short story in Spanish-America in the 19th and 20th centuries. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">RQ: Spanish 301, 302, 330 or consent. Meets: LNOR. Scheduled: Spring, even years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s333"></A>
<h3>333 Spanish-American Novel 3 </h3>
<p>The major currents in the contemporary Spanish-American novel with emphasis on selected 20th Century works. Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Spanish 301, 302, 330 or consent. Meets: LNOR. Scheduled: Fall, odd years. </a></p>
<A NAME="s495"></A>
<h3>495 Senior Seminar 4 </h3>
<p>Conducted in Spanish. <a href="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: Sr. Meets: N. Scheduled: Spring, yearly. </a></p>
<hr>
<p><a href="http://www.rockford.edu/welcome.html">Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</a> </p>
