<HEAD>
<TITLE>Religious Studies Detailed Course Descriptions</TITLE>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<H1>Rockford College<BR>
Department of Religious Studies</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<H2>Detailed Course Descriptions</H2>
<HR>
<A NAME="107"></A>
<H3>107 Hebrew Scriptures (Old Testament)	3</H3>
<P>The theological, ethical, literary and historical content of
the Old Testament in the light of modern scholarship. Attention
is given to the methods and problems of interpreting Old
Testament materials, their historical meaning, and their
contemporary significance. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">
PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="108"></A>
<H3>108 New Testament	3</H3>
<P>The theological, ethical, literary, and historical content of
the New Testament in the light of modern scholarship. Attention
is given to the methods and problems of interpreting New
Testament materials, their historical meaning and their
contemporary significance.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">
 PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="111"></A>
<H3>111 World Religions	3</H3>
<P>The historical origins and highlights, basic teachings and
practices of Hinduism, Buddhism, Taoism, Confucianism, Judaism,
Christianity, and Islam. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">
PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="211"></A>
<H3>211 History of Judaism	3</H3>
<P>The major ideas, institutions and figures in the historical
development of Judaism.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">
 PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Spring, odd years.</A>

<A NAME="212"></A>
<H3>212 History of Christianity	3</H3>
<P>The major eras in the development of Christian thought and
the life of the church. Selected writings of important
theologians from the times of the early church, the medieval
synthesis, the Reformation, the Enlightenment, and
nineteenth-century theology will be the focus of lectures and
discussions. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">
PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Spring, even years.</A>

<A NAME="301"></A>
<H3>301 Christianity in Britain to 1500	3</H3>
<P>To be offered only at Regent's College.

<A NAME="302"></A>
<H3>302 Christianity in Britain: Reformation to 1800 	3</H3>
<P>To be offered only at Regent's College.

<A NAME="315"></A>
<H3>315 Twentieth Century Theology	3</H3>
<P>A descriptive-critical survey of some of the most important
developments in 20th-century Judaeo-Christian thought through
lectures and analysis of texts selected from representative
theologians such as Barth, Tillich, Rahner, Gutierraz.<A
HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Fall, odd years.</A>

<A NAME="330"></A>
<H3>330 Religious Classics	3</H3>
<P>Students will read great books from various periods in a
prominent tradition of one or more of the world's principal
religions.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm">
 PRQ: None. Meets: LO. Scheduled: Spring, even years.</A>

<P>
<STRONG>Affiliated courses from other departments</STRONG><BR>

A/S 321 Sociology of Religion		4 hours<BR>
Art 346 Medieval Art	        	3 hours<BR>
Clas 111 Mythology			2 hours<BR>
Gr 112 New Testament Greek		3 hours<BR>
Hist 312 Renaissance and Reformation    4 hours<BR>
Phil 256 Biomedical Ethics		3 hours<BR>
Phil 329 Philosophy of Religion		3 hours<BR>
Psych 346 History and Systems of Psychology   4 hours<BR>
Special Studies (as appropriate)<BR>
</P>



