<HEAD>
<TITLE>How to read course descriptions</TITLE>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1>How to read course descriptions</H1>
<HR>

<h3>Qualifiers:</h3>
<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm#prq">PRQ</A> ...
<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm#class">Classified</A> ...
<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm#meets">Meets</A> ...
<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm#sched">Scheduled</A>

<HR>
<p><h4>Course descriptions are listed by major in the 
following sections, using this general format:</h4>

<pre>
<b>A   B                             C
101 Understanding the Nuclear Age 3
D</b>This course provides the background to make informed decisions in
our nuclear age. Topics include the structure of the atom, the nucleus,
fission, fusion, nuclear power, nuclear weapons, radioactivity, 
radioisotopes, nuclear winter. Visual aids used. Laboratory involves 
illustrations of concepts as well as data collection, graphics, etc.
PRQ: None. Classified: T. Meets: M. Scheduled: On request.


A   <b>Course number</b>  Unless otherwise noted, the course is from
    the department under which it is listed. The number tells the 
    level of the course.

B   <b>Course title</b>  The name by which the course is known; 
    generally gives an indication of the course content. 

C   <b>Course credit</b> The number of credit hours granted for
    successful completion of the course.

D   <b>Course description</b> This paragraph provides a brief 
    description and details the academic requirements of the course. 


<h4>The items at the end of the course description are:</h4>
<A NAME="prq"></A>
<b>PRQ</b>: The prerequisites for taking this course. 
They may include successful completion of other courses, certain
academic standing, instructor's permission, or other qualifications.
<A NAME="class"></A>
<b>Classified</b>: Type of course; see codes list.
<A NAME="meets"></A>
<b>Meets</b>: The General Education Requirements to which this 
course applies; see codes list.
<A NAME="sched"></A>
<b>Scheduled</b>: Indicates the planned offering of this 
course to aid in preparing a program of study. Scheduling
information is subject to the availability of faculty to teach 
courses in specific terms and may be changed without advance notice.


<h3>Course description information codes</h3>

A   Fulfills Arts requirement
B   Studio course
C   Includes Community Based Learning component
E   Freshman English course
F   Fulfills foreign language requirement for B.A. degree
L   Fulfills Language & Literature requirement
M   Fulfills Science and Mathematics requirement
N   May be used for major requirement
O   May be used for minor requirement
R   Approved as Third World course
S   Fulfills Social Science requirement
T   Lab Science course
U   Fulfills UDRWOPS requirement
X   Does not count toward 124 hours required for graduation

</pre>

<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/welcome.html">
Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</A>
