</DOCHDR>
<HTML>

<HEAD>
<Title>Rockford College FA Info</title>
<BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu">
</head>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#251899" vlink="#870999">
<a NAME ="TOP"></a>

<hr>
<H1 align="center">Rockford College </h1>

<h2 align="center">Financial Aid Information</h2>
<hr>

<ul>
	<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#AI">Application Information</a>
	<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Ver">Verification</a>
	<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#SC">Special Conditions</a>
		<UL><li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#DS">Dependent Students</a>
		<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#IS">Independent Students</a></UL>
	<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#AL">Award Letters</a>
	<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#FAO">The Financial Aid Office</a>
	<li><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#RR">Rights and Responsibilities</a>



<h2><a Name="AI">Application Information</a></h2>
<p>Renewal Applicants: The Renewal Free Application for Federal Student Aid will be sent to the address you entered on your 1995-96 application. It will show the information you provided at that time. Respond only to those questions where information has changed since your last application. Leave the spaces blank wherever the information provided is still correct.</p>

<p>April 15, 1996 is the priority application deadline. The Rockford College Financial Aid Application and the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) should be completed correctly and submitted by April 15, 1996. Late, incomplete or inaccurate applications could result in a delay in processing or lost eligibility for funds.</p>

<p>Complete the Rockford College Financial Aid Application and the FAFSA at the same time. In most cases, you will need to use both your own and your parent(s) 1995 Federal Income Tax Returns to ensure consistency of information on both forms.</p>

<p>A Financial Aid Transcript (FAT) is required from all postsecondary institutions you attended, even if you have not applied for or received aid at this institution. Another FAT is not required if you have attended Rockford College consecutively since your initial enrollment. We will request the initial FAT(s) on your behalf.</p>

<p>We encourage applicants to keep copies of all documents submitted.</p>

<p>Be certain that your Social Security number is correct when you put it on your applications or on any documentation that you submit later.</p>

<p>Financial Aid cannot be awarded, or any loans processed, until the Financial Aid Office has received all of the following:</p>

<ul>
<LI>FATs from all previously attended schools

<LI>Rockford College Financial Aid application
</ul>

<li>The results of the FAFSA (We receive the FAFSA results)
<p><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Top">Return to the top of the page</a></p> 
<p></P>
<h2><a Name="Ver">Verification</a></h2>

<p>Verification: The Higher Education Act of 1965 mandates that some applicants for federal student aid are selected for a process called Verification.</p>

<p>Verification is a procedure where a school is required to check the information a student reported on the FAFSA. Schools must verify students selected for verification by the federal central processing system, following procedures established by federal regulations. The contractor prints an asterisk next to the Expected Family Contribution (EFC) on the Student Aid Report (SAR) to identify students selected for verification.</p>

<p>If you are selected for verification, you will be required to submit a signed copy of yours and your parents, if applicable, 1995 Federal Income Tax return, including all schedules and W2 forms, and to complete a verification worksheet.</p>

<p>Federal Income Tax returns, including all schedules and W2 forms, will be required for all Special Condition/Re-evaluation requests.</p>

<p>Other documents may be requested by the Financial Aid Office, on an individual basis.</p>

<p>Complete all forms accurately. Write legibly, use black ink. Forms completed or signed in pencil or lacking the necessary signature(s) will be returned.</p>

<p>When completing the forms:</p>

<ul>
<LI>Read the instructions carefully.

<LI>Sign and date both applications. If applicable, your parent(s) or spouse should also sign in the appropriate places.

<LI>Enter 001748 Rockford College, Rockford, IL at section H #92 on the FAFSA.</p>

<LI>If you have questions or doubts about any of your answers on either application, contact the Financial Aid Office.
</ul>
<p>Students applying for financial aid for the summer 1997 session are advised to contact the Financial Aid Office between March 1, 1997 and April 1, 1997.</p>
<p><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Top">Return to the top of the page</a></p> 
<p></P>


<h2><a Name="SC">Special Conditions</a></h2>

<p>
If unusual family circumstances exist, you may complete a reevaluation form. The following list includes circumstances for dependent and independent students that are reasons for reevaluation of financial aid. You will be asked to provide letters from employers verifying expected earnings. The reevaluation form further explains the verification that will be required.
</p>

<h3><a Name="DS">	Dependent Student</a></h3>

<ul>
	<LI>A parent will have a significant decrease in income in 1996.
	<LI>You have already applied for financial aid, and since that time your parents have legally separated or divorced.
	<LI>You have already applied for financial aid, and since that time a parent has died.
	<LI>You, the student, will have a significant decrease in income in 1996.
	<LI>Your parent(s) paid medical/dental expenses in 1995 that exceeded five percent of their total income for 1995 (and were not covered by insurance).
	<LI>You have book, supply, and material or lab fees that are required for a course(s) and that exceed $800 for the academic year.
	<LI>You have travel costs for a required commute to and from campus that exceed $792 for the academic year.
</ul>

<h3><a Name="IS">	Independent Student</a></h3>

<ul>
	<LI>You and your spouse will have a significant decrease in income in 1996.
	<LI>You have already applied for financial aid, and since that time you have legally separated or divorced.
	<LI>You paid medical/dental expenses in 1995 that exceeded five percent of your total income for 1995 (and were not covered by insurance).
	<LI>You have book, supply, and material or lab fees that are required for a course(s) and that exceed $800 for the academic year.
	<LI>You have dependent child care expenses as a result of attending school.
</ul>

<p>
Note: FAFSA verification must be completed before the special condition form will be reviewed. A new Financial Aid Award Letter will be mailed to you if awards are revised as a result of the reevaluation. Applying for a reevaluation does not waive your responsibility for meeting direct costs.
</p>
<p><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Top">Return to the top of the page</a></p> 
<p></P>

<h2><a Name="AL">Award Letters</a></h2>

<p>
1996-97 Financial Aid Award Letters are mailed to the student after the financial aid application has been reviewed. If you submitted accurate applications on time, you should receive an award letter by mid-May. This date may vary and is subject to change. Appropriate student loan applications will be included with your award letter.
</p>
<p><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Top">Return to the top of the page</a></p> 

<h2><a Name="FAO">The Financial Aid Office</a></h2>
<p></P>

<p>
The Financial Aid Office follows federal and state financial aid guidelines. The Financial Aid Office provides information and advice to Rockford College students and their families who feel they are unable to meet college expenses. The Financial Aid Office is open between 8 a.m. and 5 p.m., Monday through Friday. You may request to speak with a staff member regarding individual questions or concerns between 8:30 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. each day. Appointments are preferred but not required. To receive confidential information regarding your financial aid, you must provide your birth date and social security number. Parents of dependent students will be required to do the same. No confidential information can be released to parents of independent students. 
</p>

<h3>
Student Service by Phone
</h3>

<p>
You may obtain general information and have specific questions answered by phone at (815) 226-4050 or (800) 892-2984. In order to receive confidential information regarding your financial aid, you must provide your birth date and social security number. Parents of dependent students may receive confidential information by providing the same student information. No confidential information can be released to parents of independent students or non-custodial parents of dependent students. Phone services are available between the hours of 8 a.m. to noon and 1 p.m. to 5 p.m., Monday through Friday.
</p>

<h3>
Request for Additional Information
</h3>

<p>
The Financial Aid Office recognizes that applying for financial aid is complicated and involves filing many different forms and applications. The Financial Aid Office will continue the practice of sending four requests for additional information to each eligible applicant when further information is required.
</p>

<p>
The primary responsibility for submitting all required forms rests with the applicant. You should review application instructions carefully.
</p>
<p><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Top">Return to the top of the page</a></p> 
<p></P>

<h2><A Name="RR">Students Financial Aid Rights and Responsibilities</A></H2>

<h3>
You have the right to:
</h3>

<UL>	
	<LI>Know the total costs of attending Rockford College, both direct and indirect expenses, and the institutions policy on refunds if you withdraw.
	<LI>Know the financial aid available and the procedures and deadlines for applying for these programs.
	<LI>Know how your financial need and your family contribution are determined.
	<LI>Ask for recalculation if you feel special circumstances should be considered.
	<LI>Know the interest rate on any student loans, the total amount you must repay, the beginning date and length of time for repayment, and cancellation or deferment policies.
	<LI>Know the hours, duties, pay rate, and how and when youll be paid if you have a College Work-Study (CWS) job.
	<LI>Know how satisfactory  progress is determined.	
</ul>

<h3>
You have the responsibility to:
</h3>

<UL>
	<li>Complete all financial aid applications accurately and on time, provide all documentation as requested by the Financial Aid Office, and notify the office of any changes.
	<LI>Read, understand, and keep copies of all forms youre asked to sign.
	<LI>Attend an entrance interview and an exit interview before leaving school.
	<LI>Repay your student loans.
	<LI>Perform the work agreed upon in a CWS job.
	<LI>Understand satisfactory progress and refund policies.
	<LI>Ask questions when in doubt about any of the financial aid information you receive.
</ul>
<p><A HREF="/finaid/fainfo1.htm#Top">Return to the top of the page</a></p> 
<p></P>
<p><A HREF="/finaid/finaid.htm">Return to the Financial Aid Home Page</a></p> 
<p></P>

