<HTML>


<HEAD>
<TITLE>British Studies Detailed Course Descriptions</TITLE>
<!-- Keep the below line commented out until loaded to Web Server -->
<!-- <BASE HREF=http://www.rockford.edu/">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>Rockford College<BR>
British Studies (Minor)</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<H2>Detailed Course Descriptions</H2>
<HR>

<PRE>
<A NAME="201"></A>
<H3>201 Survey of English Literature I      3</H3>
<P>A survey of major works and authors from the Old English period to 
the Restoration (c. 750-1660); includes special consideration of the 
historical development of the English language. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm"> 
PRQ: Eng 112 or equivalent. Meets: LNO. Scheduled: Fall, yearly.</A>


<A NAME="202"></A>
<H3>202 Survey of English Literature II      3</H3>
<P>A survey of representative works and authors from the Restoration 
to the twentieth century. PRQ: Eng 112 or equivalent. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm"> 
Meet: LNO. Scheduled: Spring, yearly.</A>

<A NAME="210"></A>
<H3>210 History of England Since the Conquest      4</H3>
<P>British civilization from a historical and developmental perspective. 
Among the topics that students will be expected to study are the Norman 
Conquest, the origin and evolution of the English Parliamentary Monarchy, 
the English Reformation, the Elizabethan Age, the Industrial Revolution, 
Imperialism, and the creation of the English welfare state. An important, 
though not exclusive, function of the course will be to prepare students 
for life and study at Regent's College. <A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm"> 
PRQ: None. Meets: SNO. Scheduled: Alternate years.</A>

<A NAME="300"></A>
<H3>300 The Civilization of London      4</H3>
<P>To be offered only at Regent's College. Advanced study in the history 
of London, organized around topics and themes that illuminate the most 
important aspects of the city's past and present.  Topics include the 
geography and physical development of the city; the history and function 
of institutions such as parliament, the law courts, the monarchy, 
the education system, and the Bank of England; the city's contribution 
to the arts, literature, philosophy and science; the sociology and 
problems of the modern megalopolis.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm"> PRQ: None. Classified: 1Y. Meets: SNOV.</A>

<A NAME="324"></A>
<H3>324 Tudor-Stuart England      4</H3>
<P>Deals predominantly with the political history of the period:  social 
and intellectual history, along with some historiograph also will be 
considered. The English Reformation and the English Civil War will be 
areas of special concern.<A HREF="/academic/catalog/codes.htm"> PRQ: None. Meets: SNO. Scheduled: Alternate years.</A>

<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/welcome.html">
Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</A>
<HR>
