<HEAD>

<TITLE>British Studies</TITLE>
<!--Keep the below line commented out until loaded to Web Server-->
<!-- <BASE HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1>Rockford College<BR>
British Studies (Minor) </H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>

<H2>Index</H2>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/academic/catalog/british/britstud.htm#overview">
Overview</A>
<LI><A HREF="/academic/catalog/british/britstud.htm#require">
Minor Requirements</A>
<LI><A HREF="/academic/catalog/british/courses.htm#courses">
Course Offerings</A>
</UL>

<A NAME="overview"><A/>
<H3>Overview</H3>

<PRE>

The minor concentration in British studies enables students to give 
distinctive focus to study at Regent's College and may be used to 
complement a variety of major programs. The minor includes a core of 
required courses, usually taken before and during a term in London, 
and elective courses which may be completed after students return to 
Rockford College.  

The minor is administered by the English Department, and the department 
chair must approve students' plans of study for the minor in British 
Studies.  Electives for the minor must be chosen from more than one 
department.  No courses which count toward students' majors may count 
as elective courses toward the British Studies minor. 

<A NAME="require"><A/>
<STRONG>Minor requirements -- 20 hours</STRONG>

Eng 201 Survey of English Literature I 3 hours
Eng 202 Survey of English Literature II     3 hours

Two of the following:

Hist 210 History of England Since the Conquest   4 hours
Hist 300 Civilization of London (Regent's College only)    4 hours
Hist 324 Tudor-Stuart England     4 hours

Elective courses: At least six hours of 200- or 300-level course-work 
which focuses substantially on Britain, chosen with approval of the chair 
of the English Department. 
</PRE>

<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.rockford.edu/welcome.html">
Return to the Rockford College Home Page.</A>
