<CENTER><H2>Venture Technology Incorporated</H2></CENTER>
<P>

<BR><HR><BR>
<CENTER>
|<A HREF="../VTI/team.html">VTI TEAM</A>
 |<A HREF="../VTI/unique.html">CAPABILITIES</A>
 |<A HREF="../VTI/caveat.html">CAVEATS</A>  
 |<A HREF="../VTI/nda.html">NDA</A> 
 |<A HREF="../VTI/client.html">CLIENTS</A> 
 |<A HREF="../VTI/remun.html">FEES</A>|
</CENTER>
<BR><HR><BR>

<H3><CENTER><IMG SRC="/Net_Gifs/Buttons/MailboxButton.gif" ALIGN="CENTER">
President<BR>
Voice: (818) 541-9788<BR>
e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:venturetech@earthlink.net">venturetech@earthlink.net</A><BR>
</CENTER></H3>
<BR><HR><BR>


<CENTER>
<H1><STRONG>How to Solve Tough Technical Problems</STRONG></H1>
</CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<P><STRONG>What Can We Do For You?</STRONG>  Our 
<A HREF="../VTI/team.html">scientists and engineers</A> solve your technical
problems by finding other technologist any where in the world that are 
<A HREF="../VTI/unique.html">uniquely capable</A> of solving your problem.  The 
<A HREF="../VTI/team.html">linguistic and technical diversity</A> 
of our technologists enable us to speak to other uniquely 
qualified technologists in their native language using the proper 
technical words of the specific technology.  This form of interaction 
allows an immediate <A HREF="../VTI/unique.html">exchange of technical knowledge</A>. 
 This professional courtesy is practised by all members of the various 
 <A HREF="../VTI/team.html">scientific and engineering disciplines</A>.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Who Is Venture Technology (VTI)?</STRONG> Over the last 30 years VTI has developed 
<A HREF="../VTI/caveat.html">consulting relationships</A> with 85 scientists and engineers.  These 
technologists are mainly employed by <A HREF="../VTI/caveat.html">national laboratories and 
universities</A>.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>How Do We Do It?</STRONG>  The <A HREF="../VTI/client.html">
potential client</A> Emails, mails or faxes VTI's or the 
client's <A HREF="../VTI/nda.html">nondisclosure agreement</A> to 
<A HREF="../VTI/unique.html">VTI's coordinator</A>.  The coordinator 
assigns the task to one or more of VTI's existing technologists and has 
them sign the nondisclosure agreement.   They discuss the <A HREF="../VTI/unique.html">nature of the 
problem</A> with the <A HREF="../VTI/client.html">potential client</A>.  They negotiate a statement of work and 
the <A HREF="../VTI/unique.html">client's coordinator and task monitor and 
VTI's coordinator and task 
manager</A> sign the statement of work.  VTI's existing technologist finds 
other technologist if required.  After making contact and validating the 
technologist suitability, the VTI existing technologist together with the 
validated technologist <A HREF="../VTI/team.html">solve the problem</A>.  The detail reports with costs 
to date are sent to the client periodically, a final invoice is sent to 
the client at the end of the task.  VTI can only accept a problem solving 
task on a best efforts basis, sometimes the problem may not be solvable.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Why Do We Do It?</STRONG> Solving difficult problems is gratifying, however, some 
<A HREF="../VTI/client.html">classes of clients</A> make it more enjoyable than others.  It supplements 
academic and research salaries.  New skills may prove useful to the 
technologists employer, without violating the client's nondisclosure 
agreement.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>How Much?</STRONG> Most of the scientists and engineers with <A HREF="../VTI/remun.html">advanced degrees</A> and 
decades of experience are <A HREF="../VTI/remun.html">paid about $100/hr</A>.


<BR><HR><BR>

<OL>

<CENTER>
<H2>The Services</H2>
</CENTER>

<BR><BR><BR>
<LI><STRONG>Solve Technical Problems.</STRONG>  VTI's network of scientists and engineers can 
solve problems that you may be having with your new or existing products 
or processes.  The solution may consist of theoretical, analytical, system 
design, detail design, feasibility demonstration or prototype fabrication 
and testing. Sometimes groups of technologists together can 
conceive of solutions to a problem that a lesser group could not.  Such a 
process is sometimes referred to as "revolutionary-system-engineering".  Most 
companies are able to perform evolutionary-system-engineering, 
sometimes called "step-by-step development".  VTI can assist in solving specific problems 
that arise in disciplines that are not available to clients own 
technologists.  VTI technologists are skilled in capturing the 
intellectual property rights that may issue from such solutions.</LI>  
<BR><BR>
<LI><STRONG>Invent New Products or Processes.</STRONG>  In many instances 
VTI's technologists 
can invent new or improved products or processes that maintain a company's 
intellectual-property-monopoly position in the market. </LI> 
<BR><BR>
<LI><STRONG>Invent Around or Beyond Competitor's Patents.</STRONG> They can invent 
improvements based upon new technology not known at the time the previous 
patents were filed.  </LI>  
<BR><BR>
<LI><STRONG>Find Patent Prior Art.</STRONG>  They can find prior art that can not be found by 
conventional searches and investigations by using technologists that find 
and consult with other technologists that may have special knowledge.  </LI>
<BR><BR>
<LI><STRONG>Evaluates Patents.</STRONG> They can provide independent technical evaluations of 
patents and/or suites of patents by technologists skilled in the art of 
the particular science or engineering discipline. </LI> 
</OL>
<BR><HR>
