<HR>
<BR>

<H2>QUIZ</H2>

<P>What four days of the week begin with the letter T?  Answer: Tuesday, 
Thursday, today and tomorrow.

<BR>
<HR>
<BR>

<P>I am in third grade at Loma Alta School.  Mrs McCarthy is my teacher, 
she has a masters degree in teaching gifted children, which is good for me 
because I have got into the GATE program (California's Gifted and Talented 
Education program for elementary and secondary schools).  
Our school gets special science education projects from Caltech, also, so 
it is very lucky.
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=5><TR><TD><IMG SRC="andy.gif">  
  </TD></TR>
</TABLE><CAPTION>This is me in my Little League uniform</CAPTION>
</CENTER>
<BR>

<P>I was born in Pasadena, California in 1989, so that makes me an 
American Citizen.  But my Mom is Scottish, so I am too.  I go to Edinburgh every 
summer to visit my Granma Hylda.  Last summer I visited the old 
battlegrounds at Stirling and Bannockburn where William Wallace and Robert 
the Bruce defeated the English armies.  

