<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Images of William Wallace and Robert the Bruce</TITLE>
<META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Christine M. Carmichael">
<META NAME="Keywords" CONTENT="Images William Wallace Robert Bruce 
Scotland History Mel Gibson Braveheart ">

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = #003333 TEXT=#FFFFFF VLINK=#996633 LINK=#996600>
<BR>

<BR>

<HR><BR><center><TABLE BORDER=5><TR><TD><IMG SRC="bw.gif">  
  </TD></TR>
</TABLE><CAPTION>Wallace and Bruce</CAPTION></center>

<BR>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/Net_Gifs/Bars/CastleWallBar.gif"></CENTER>
<BR>

  <H3><BR> It is unlikely that they ever met in real life. 
   Although both were Scottish patriots who 
fought the English during the 18-year War of Independence (1296 - 1314), 
they supported different political factions.  Wallace wanted to reinstate 
John Baliol as King of Scotland, and Bruce wanted his father to be King.
In this mural, Wallace and Bruce stand together on the walls of the 
Scottish Museum of Antiquities, Edinburgh, Scotland. 
If you ever visit Scotland you must see this wonderful little museum just 
down the hill a couple of blocks from Princes Street and Waverly Station.

If you would like to see more of this mural click<A HREF="kings.html">here.</A>  
</H3><BR> 
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/Net_Gifs/Bars/CastleWallBar.gif"></CENTER>

<BR>
<CENTER><A HREF="Scenes6.html">Return to the previous page</A></CENTER>

