<BODY BACKGROUND="artBG.gif">



<CENTER><H1>ARTAFACE</H1></CENTER>

<CENTER><H2>Your Face in Art</H2></CENTER><P>
<BR> 
 
<P>This makes a really delightful gift for anyone.  All you need is
 a color photograph of the person you want to surprise.  They need never know what you 
 are planning until you give them a lovely framed print, or poster with 
 their portrait in a famous painting. 
<BR>   
<P>Below you will see an example of how the face from a modern day photo 
can be incorporated into a famous work of art. We can do the same for you if you send us a (paper/color photo) copy of the 
art you want modified and the photo of the person to be inserted.  It is 
important that each of these show the same view of the face in order to produce 
the best results.  In the first example both the faces are both slightly 
turned away from the viewer.  Neither is full-on, neither is in profile.  
Please follow this rule when sending us the two pictures you want us to 
combine.  Choose the photograph to match the painted face carefully, in order to 
ensure the best results.  You might consider asking a friend to take a photo of 
you posed in the same position, with the light coming from the same 
direction as in the painting of your choice.<BR><BR>

<HR><BR><center><TABLE BORDER=5><TR><TD><IMG SRC="renoir.gif">  
  </TD></TR>
</TABLE><CAPTION>Detail from painting by Renoir </CAPTION>

<TABLE BORDER=5><TR><TD>  
  <IMG SRC="fra.gif"></TD></TR>
</TABLE><CAPTION>Photo of young woman </CAPTION>
<TABLE BORDER=5><TR><TD>  
  <IMG SRC="renfra.gif"></TD></TR>
</TABLE><CAPTION>Put them together--Voila!.</CAPTION></center>

<BR>
<P>The lucky recipient of your thoughtful gift will glow with
 delight when he or she sees the results of this process -- 
 our newest style of photo  enhancement.<BR>
<P>To give you some ideas, here are more examples of what we can do:
<BR><BR>
