|<A HREF="authorsM.html"><STRONG>M</STRONG></A>: C.C. MacApp-Peter Morwood
|<A HREF="authorsN.html"><STRONG>N</STRONG></A>: Vladimir Nabokov-Jody Lynn Nye
|<A HREF="authorsO.html"><STRONG>O</STRONG></A>: Hermann Oberth-Mark Owings
|<A HREF="authorsP.html"><STRONG>P AND Q</STRONG></A>: Lewis Padgett-Seabury Quinn
|<A HREF="authorsR.html"><STRONG>R</STRONG></A>: John Rackham-Olivia Ruuderman
|<A HREF="authorsS.html"><STRONG>S</STRONG></A>: Fred Saberhagen-Michael Swanwick
|<A HREF="authorsT.html"><STRONG>T</STRONG></A>: Judith Tarr-Mark Twain
|<A HREF="authorsUV.html"><STRONG>U AND V</STRONG></A>: Rochelle M. Uhlenkott-Ray Vukcevich
|<A HREF="authorsW.html"><STRONG>W</STRONG></A>: C. C. Waddell--Ed Wyrick
|<A HREF="authorsXYZ.html"><STRONG>X, Y, Z</STRONG>: </A>"X, Ex-Private"- END


<A HREF="http://www.Catch22.Com/SF/">Alpha Ralpha Boulevard</A>, 
     formerly known as Espana's Science Fiction Authors Page
     which offers free Web pages for persons active in Science Fiction
<A HREF="http://www.oneworld.net/SF/authors/">Oneworld's Science Fiction Authors Page</A>, 
     which offers free Web pages for persons active in Science Fiction
<A HREF="http://www.sff.net">SFF-NET's Science Fiction Authors Page</A>, 
     which offers free Web pages for persons active in Science Fiction
Author, Author			to be done
<A HREF="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu:80/hypertext/faq/usenets/sf/top.html">
Science Fiction Authors Maintainers	(LINK #1)</A>
<A HREF="http://un-gna.mit.edu:8001/uu-gna/schools/vslis/topics/Literature/Science%20Fiction">Science Fiction Authors Maintainers	(LINK #2)</A>

Some data on authors NOT linked on the World Wide Web is based upon "The 
Encyclopedia of Science Fiction and Fantasy, Through 1968", compiled by 
Donald H. Tuck, Chicago: Advent Publishers, Inc., 1974.  I recommend this 
encyclopedia, as well as more recent and comprehensive encyclopediae 
including the one available on CD-ROM by Peter Nichols and John Clute.

See also "Science Fiction: The 100 Best Novels, an English Language 
     Selection 1949-1984", by David Pringle (London: Carroll & Graf, 1985)
     for interesting analysis of 100 readable, excellent, significant books
     
See also "Dream Makers: The Uncommon People Who Write Science Fiction", 
     interviews by Charles Platt (New York: Berkeley, 1980)

See also "Bibliography of Science Fiction and Fantasy" by Sam J. Lundwall, 1964, 
     which I believe has been updated in at least three editions.  He also 
     provided important information in "Science Fiction: fran begynnelsen till 
     vara dagar", commissioned by Radio Sweden, and published in 1969.  The 
     English translation is "Science Fiction: What It's All About", Sam J. 
     Lundwall, New York: Ace, 1971.
     
See also "Billion Year Spree: The True History of Science Fiction", Brian W. 
     Aldiss, (New York: Doubleday, 1973; Schocken Paperback, 1974)
     
See also "Asimov on Science Fiction" (New York: Avon, 1981)

There are several sources for pseudonyms listed here (so far mostly A-P and W-Z):

     "The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction and Fantasy, Through 1968", compiled by 
      Donald H. Tuck, Chicago: Advent Publishers, Inc., 1974
    
      "Checklist of Fantastic Literature", Bleiler, 1948
      
      NFFF Listings of the 1950s
      
      J. Page's list in "Lore" (Sep 1966)
      
     "Sciencefiction and Fantasy Pseudonyms", Barry McGhan, 1976
      
     "Who Goes There", James Rock, 1979
      
     "Index to the Science Fiction Magazines 1926-1950", D. B. Day, 1952
      
     "The Index of Science Fiction Magazines 1951-1965", N. Metcalf, 1968
      
     "The Hero-Pulp Index", L. McKinstry & R. Weinberg, 1970
      
     "Stella Nova", R. Regnald, 1970
      
     "Who's Who in Horror and Fantasy Fiction", M. Ashley, 1977
      
     "Twentieth Century Science Fiction Writers", C. V. Smith, 1981
      
     "Science Fiction and Fantasy Literature", R. Reginald, 1979

98 hotlinks were compiled for Dragon*Con 1997, and hotlinks to them are 
     designated "@ Dragon*Con" and provided here by permission of 
     Edward E. Kramer, Convention Chairman, as of 19 Sep 1996

