<A NAME="COUNTRIES-BELGIUM"><STRONG><H3>BELGIUM</H3></STRONG></A>
A good biographical/bibliographical reference is "Early Birds", by Michel 
Feron and Danny de Laet (1970).  They list writers and fans including:
     Frans Buyens
     Danny DeLaet
     Michel Feron
     Michael Grayn, pseudonym of Michel Englebert, publisher of Atlanta
     Theo Muet
     Edgar B. Jacobs
     Raymond de Kremer (perhaps the major SF/Weird author in Belgium)
     Hubert Lampo: Dutch/Flemish magical realist
     Thomas Owen
     Henri-Jacques Proumen
     Marcel Thiry
     Albert Van Hageland, editor, author, promoter
     Paul VanHerck
     Jos Van Limbergen
     Horace Van Offel
     Leopold Vermeiren: the Jules Verne of Belgium?

Magazines include:
     Anticipations, Belgium (in French), (Sep 1945-May 1946): nothing on the Web?
     Atlanta, Belgium (in French) (Jan 1966-?): nothing on the Web?
     Utopia: nothing on the Web?

Belgium, by the way, is one of the 8 countries that accesses the 
Magic Dragon web domain often, at least 10-20 days per month on the average. 
Belgium first "hit" this domain in April 1996.

