<A NAME="COUNTRIES-EGYPT"><STRONG><H3>EGYPT</H3></STRONG></A>

I don't know anything about Science Fiction in Egypt, other than the 
various science fiction novels which are based on Egyptian mythology.  The 
two best of these, in my opinion, are "CReatures of Light and Darkness" by 
Roger Zelazny, and "Ancient Evenings" by Norman Mailer (whom I had met as a 
child, at a party in his Columbia Heights apartment in Brooklyn).  

Egypt has, of course, produced great writers, including the recent Nobel 
Laureate Mafouz -- does any of his work have a science fiction or fantasy 
element?  I don't know.

Won't somebody who knows something e-mail an entry to put here?
     
