<P><H2><CENTER>The Personal English Company</CENTER></H2></P>

<HR>

<P><H3><CENTER>
HISTORY AND MISSION OF THE PERSONAL ENGLISH COMPANY
</CENTER></H3>

The Personal English Company, based near Los Angeles in Sierra Madre, 
California, U.S.A., was founded in 1984 to provide advanced English language 
training and materials to foreign-born professionals working in American 
public and private sector organizations.  A wide variety of English language 
video and audio taped materials are now available.  The design and content of 
these materials is based on more than a decade of intensive research into 
the unique needs of professional men and women who speak English as a second 
language.  Persons from many different professions have benefitted from PEC's 
language programs and tapes: engineers; data processing and information systems 
professionals; doctors, nurses, and medical technicians; bankers; 
administrators and managers of public and private companies; diplomats; 
foreign businessmen and  businesswomen; secretaries and clerical professionals.
</P>

<HR>

<P>
<H2><CENTER>P.E.C. FOUNDER AND PRESIDENT</CENTER></H2>
<H3>
<CENTER>CHARLOTTE BLACKMON COLLINS:  WOMAN WITH A MISSION</CENTER>
</H3>
</P>

<P>
<BR CLEAR='all'><IMG SRC="Charlotte.gif" ALIGN="LEFT">
Founder and president, <STRONG>Charlotte Blackmon Collins</STRONG>, English 
Language Specialist, 
is a professional trainer and consultant to numerous local, regional, 
national
 and international companies and government agencies.  With a background in
 business education, teaching English as a second language, and 
intercultural studies, she founded The Personal English Company in 1984 
after noting the  lack of English language training programs and materials 
for foreign-born
 professionals who hoped to advance in their careers.  She observed that
 technically competent professionals became stuck at a level below their 
 true potential -- and were unable to achieve promotions into management  
-- because of English language deficits in pronunciation, vocabulary and 
 writing.  During 12 years of dedicated study and observation, she has 
 produced and published English language audio and video tapes designed 
 to ensure professionals career advancement through improved 
pronounciation of Standard American English and extensive vocabulary  
development in common and technical vocabularies.
</P>
<P> On June 21, 1996, the Summer Solstice, Charlotte Blackmon was married 
to Dr. Clyde Collins, the architect of <A 
HREF="http://www.magicdragon.com">Magic Dragon</A> and the owner of <A 
HREF="http://www.magicdragon.com/HaversineEnterprises">Haversine 
Enterprises,</A> in a garden wedding in <A 
HREF="wedding.html">Sierra Madre, California.</A>
<HR>

