<LI><A NAME="Idioms That Use Prepositions I">
<STRONG>Idioms That Use Prepositions I</STRONG></A></LI>
<A HREF="index.html#Pronunciation">Main Catalog</A>

<P>Two audio tapes contain American English idioms made up of a verb and a 
preposition, such as: "made of," "made up of," "in trouble with," "in relation 
to," and many others.  The meaning of each idiom is clearly described and 
example sentences demonstrate how each one is used.  A manual is included with 
the boxed set. <STRONG>$20.00</STRONG></P>

