<P><H2><CENTER>PAS SPECIAL SERVICES</CENTER></H2></P>
<BR>


<P> These procedures are for the benefit of arbitrators and mediators who 
operate independently, (not under the rules of any organization providing 
ADR services) but do not have the administrative staff to assist them in 
the clerical details required to administer the proceedings. 
<BR>


<P> <STRONG>Pacific ADR</STRONG> will handle all administration required to:
<BR>

<UL>
<LI> Schedule the time and place of hearing(s).<BR>
<LI> Collect fees in advance for arbitrator/mediator compensation.<BR>
<LI> Collect fees in advance for hearing rooms, if required.<BR>
<LI> Handle all correspondence, document transmittal etc. between 
arbitrator/mediators and parties.<BR>
<LI> Close file with written notification to all concerned with accounting 
of funds deposited and a refund, if any, of unused fees and costs.<BR>
<LI> There is no cost to arbitrator/mediator for this service.  Parties 
will be billed separately at the rate of $40.00 per hour for the time of 
the hearing based on a six hour day with a maximum fee of $400.00.  In the 
event of prolonged hearings, if there is a hiatus, subsequent hearings 
will be billed as a separate proceedings.<BR>
<LI> Postponement fees will be billed at $40.00 per hour for actual time 
spent in rescheduling.<BR>
</UL>

