<CENTER>
<H1>Process Details and Caveats</H1>
</CENTER>

<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Conflicts of Interest.</STRONG>  VTI has cultivated consulting-technologists that 
are aware of the problems with working for more that one entity at a time 
without breaching confidential boundaries.  VTI is very sensitive to 
potential conflicts of interest.  In 30 year, VTI has avoided damaging a 
client's interests.  On a few occasions VTI has had to terminate a 
relationship because of a real or perceived conflict.  <BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>1099.</STRONG>  VTI's pool of scientists and engineers are all 1099 independent 
consultants to VTI.  They have their own home office, computers, and other 
tools.   They pay their own out-of-pocket-expenses which may be reimburse 
by VTI.  Most of them have served VTI clients in the past.  Many of the 
newer members were recruited by the senior members.  Some have only 
consulted for VTI once, some have solved many problems over the years.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Reputations.</STRONG>  VTI's trusted technologists are almost all professional 
degreed scientists or engineers who are very protective of their 
reputations.  They are part of self-validating groups that will not 
sacrifice their professional reputations for short-term gain.  Their 
reputation is their most important asset.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>A Body-Contact Sport.</STRONG>  VTI has no agreement with any of the technologists, 
and they are free to consult or work for anyone they chose on their own, 
even VTI's clients.  VTI encourages one-on-one relationships with the 
client or the client's technologist.  Many have done just that.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Not A Job-Shop or Employment Agent.</STRONG>  VTI is not a job-shop contractor.  
The VTI technologists are valued for their knowledge and unique skills.  
VTI can help the client to locate and validate the appropriate 
technologists for a particular long term relationship.  But, VTI cannot 
efficiently compete with employment agencies.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Patent Attorneys & Reputations.</STRONG>  Most of the relationships that VTI has 
had with corporations has been through their patent attorney or patent 
firm.  Patent attorneys are usually aware of their clients technical and 
intellectual property needs.  The also can validate and guide the 
relationship between their client and technologists that they are 
acquainted with.  This relationship also extends to other patent law 
firms.  Technologists know that their reputations, good or bad, can travel 
throughout the intellectual property community to the benefit or the 
detriment of their valuable reputations.  This is the most important part 
of this extended network that will not work without mutual trust.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>
Best Efforts. </STRONG> VTI can only provide a best-efforts commitment to its 
clients.  The application of standard textbook solutions to a problem can 
usually be guaranteed, innovative solutions cannot.  If technologists 
skilled in the art could solve the problem by the application of 
previously know methodologies, then it is unlikely that the solution rises 
to the level of a patentable intellectual property.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>
Innovative Solutions.</STRONG>  Developing inventive solutions to problems implies 
that the solution to the problem is not amenable to conventional technical 
solutions.  VTI has always left the standard solutions to the many fine 
engineering firms in the country.  VTI can find and recommend such firms. 
VTI's motto is <BR>

<CENTER>
<I>"If we knew how to do it then we should not be doing it.</I></CENTER>

<BR>  

