<H1>Proprietary Information Nondisclosure Agreement</H1>
</CENTER>


<BR>
Effective Date: ___________________ 
In order to protect Information (as defined below) that may be disclosed 
by Discloser (identified below) to the Recipient (identified below) the 
Discloser and the Recipient agree that: 
<BR><UL>
<LI>This <STRONG>Agreement</STRONG> controls only <STRONG>Information</STRONG> which is disclosed between the 
<STRONG>Effective Date</STRONG> above and the <STRONG>End of Disclosing Date</STRONG>: ____________
</LI><BR>


<LI>The Recipient shall use the Information only for the purpose of: 
_________________________________________________
_________________________________________________</LI>
<LI>The Recipient's duty to protect Information disclosed under this Agreement 
expires on the End of Nondisclosure Date: ____________ </LI>
<LI>The Recipient agrees to care for the Information using the same protection 
that it uses to protect its own Information. </LI>
<LI>The Recipient agrees not to disclose said Information to a third party, 
except solely for purposes of this Agreement, and only in confidence and 
upon a "need-to-know" basis.</LI>
<LI>Information shall be defined as proprietary, confidential, or intellectual 
property rights disclosed to the Recipient:</LI>
     <LI>The Information includes the written description under the heading 
       Information below and any attachments.</LI>  
      <LI>The Information disclosed in oral, graphic or other non-written form shall 
      be summarized in writing by the Discloser and attached to this Agreement 
      and transmitted to the Recipient within fifteen (30) days of such initial 
      disclosure.  The Summary shall describe when and to whom the Information 
      was disclosed. </LI>
      <LI>The Information shall be marked to identify it as having proprietary, 
      confidential, or intellectual property rights. </LI> 
<LI>The foregoing obligations shall not apply to information which the 
Recipient can demonstrate falls within one of the following 6 exceptions:</LI>  
<LI>The information is or becomes available to the public through publication, 
inspection of product or otherwise, without the fault of Recipient.</LI>   
<LI>The information was known to or independently developed by Recipient.</LI>   
<LI>The information was received without an obligation of confidentially from 
a third party. </LI>  
<LI>The information is disclosed by Discloser to a third party without similar 
restrictions on the third party.  </LI>
<LI>The information is approved for release or use by written authorization of 
Discloser.  </LI>
<LI>The disclosure of the information is required or obligated by a government 
agency, legislative body or court of competent jurisdiction.</LI> 
<LI> The Discloser warrants that it has the right to disclose Information under 
this Agreement.  </LI>
<LI>Neither party may use the other party's name in any advertisement or 
selling program, nor will either party directly or indirectly refer to the 
other party without prior written approval of the other, except to the 
extent required to perform this Agreement.</LI>
<LI>This Agreement does not convey any rights in Discloser's know-how, patents 
or other intellectual property rights to the Recipient.</LI>
<LI>The Recipient shall return to Discloser, upon request, any and all written 
documents provided under this Agreement and Recipient agrees, that it will 
not copy or reproduce in whole or in part any such documents without 
<LI>Discloser's written permission, except one copy that may be retained for 
archival purposes.</LI>
<LI>This document contains the entire Agreement of the parties and supersedes 
any previous or contemporaneous agreement.  Modification of this Agreement 
shall only be binding if made in writing and signed by both parties.
<LI>This Agreement is made under and shall be construed according to the laws 
of the State of California, USA.</LI>
<LI>Additional Recipients and/or Disclosers must sign duplicates of this 
Agreement. </LI> 
</LI>Signing of Faxed Agreements is with the understanding that the originals 
shall be mailed to all parties within 10 working days. </LI>
</UL>
<BR><BR><HR><BR>
(This Signature and Information description page must be on the other side 
of the paper for this to be considered an original or 
a copy of the original Agreement.  If you are not associated with a 
company or other entity ignore the Company Name line.)

