<CENTER>
<H1>Preferred Relationships with Clients</H1>
</CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Patent Law Firms Preferred.</STRONG>  VTI prefers to work for patent law firms that 
have clients that require solutions to one of the above problems.  Such a 
relationship is based upon mutual validated trust between the parties.  
See below for more details.
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Clients Recommended to VTI by Patent Law Firms.</STRONG>  VTI has provided 
technical consultants for the corporate patent counsel of several very 
large high tech companies, one for 10 years and another for 20 years.  It 
has consulted directly for the president and owner of companies.  It has 
provided all the technologists for several small companies for over ten 
years.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>LAIPLA Referrals.</STRONG>  Up until the last two years, VTI has not acquired any 
new clients that were not recommended to it by a present client.  As the 
result of an invited presentation given to the Los Angeles Intellectual 
Property Law Association in 1995, several new clients have requested VTI's 
services.  
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Prefers Established Clients.</STRONG>  VTI prefers to work for successful companies 
that have demonstrated skills in management, marketing, manufacturing and 
finance.  


