<CENTER><H1>American Competitiveness Enterprise, Inc.</H1></CENTER>

<BR><I><CENTER>Strategic technology planning isn't deciding what to do in the future;
</CENTER>
<CENTER>It's deciding what to do now in order to have a future!</CENTER></I>
<BR>
<H3>Can your corporation provide all your technology requirements internally?</H3>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>The growth of technology is accelerating</LI>
<LI>Technology fields have become numerous, diverse, and specialized </LI> 
<LI>Technologists are increasingly specialized</LI>
<LI>Technological expertise is spread worldwide</LI>
<LI>Company response time to technical opportunities and problems are critical to strategic
 success</LI>
</UL>
<BR>
<H3>ACE offers you the opportunity to outsource selected technology needs</H3>


<P>We have developed, over the past twenty years of technology commercialization 
activities, an unrivaled world-wide network of technologists to meet company technology 
requirements.</P><BR><BR>



<H3>ACE offers the tools and services to address your technology needs:</H3>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Outsource technologists to solve problems</LI>
<LI>Executive workshops on technology evaluation and planning</LI>
<LI>Strategic technology planning</LI>
<LI>Technology alliance development</LI>
<LI>Technology acquisitions</LI>
<LI>Patent development</LI>
<LI>Patent defense strategiest</LI>
<LI>Corporate information and communications development</LI>
<LI>Internet website development</LI>
</UL>
<BR>
<CENTER<H2><STRONG>Key ACE Executives</STRONG>  --  Vita available</H2></CENTER>
<CENTER<H3>Over 100 years of combined public and private technology 
commercialization experience</H3></CENTER><BR>

<CENTER>Thomas L. Walters, President</CENTER>
<CENTER>John E. McDonald, Chairman of the Board of Directors</CENTER>
<CENTER>Christine Carmichael, Director of Patent Analysis</CENTER>
<CENTER>Aurora Chamberlain, Director of Corporate Development</CENTER>
<CENTER>Kenneth Ito, Director of Corporate Collaboration and Acquisitions</CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER>Phone: 818/541-9788;    E-mail: venturetech@earthlink.net</CENTER><BR>
<CENTER>Consultant Costs Range from $720 - $2500 per day, depending on the 
task and the personnel</CENTER>
<BR><HR><BR>


<CENTER>
<H2><STRONG>Examples of services performed by ACE personnel</STRONG></H2>
</CENTER><BR>

(some details have been changed to protect the identity of client companies)
<BR><BR><STRONG>Outsource technologists to solve problems</STRONG>  --  The production
 line of Company A ground to a halt when circuit boards began shorting.  Within two days
  the ACE expert had identified the problem as a conformal coating which had some 
  conducting properties.  A new coating was acquired, and a quality control program 
  initiated.  Problem solved, and future problems prevented.
<BR><BR><STRONG>Executive workshops on technology evaluations and planning</STRONG>  -- 
Executives at Company D recognized the need 
 to tap technology outside the corporation to improve its production line, but there 
 was no corporate experience in working with universities or government laboratories.  
 Workshops and strategic planning sessions assisted company to reorganize to use contract
  technologists to reduce manufacturing and quality control costs.
<BR><BR><STRONG>Technology alliance development</STRONG>   --  Company B sought expertise in cryptology to 
develop a new product. We arranged for the technology to be developed at a government 
laboratory.  Costs were much less than developing a new laboratory and hiring expertise.
<BR><BR><STRONG>Technology acquisitions</STRONG>  --  Company C sought a new product 
to strengthen its medical diagnostic product line.  The ACE consultant evaluated potential acquisitions without
 releasing the identity of the company or its corporate strategy.  Options were 
 developed, complementary product identified, and acquisition completed.<BR>
<BR><STRONG>Patent strategy</STRONG> --  Company F was being sued for patent infringement.  ACE 
 consultants identified prior art the patent of questions, thereby stopping the 
 infringement suit.

 <BR><BR>
<STRONG>Corporate communications systems</STRONG>  --  Executives at Company G desired briefing on improving 
internal communications, and marketing options available through an Internet website.  
Through a workshop, corporate information strategy was devised, and a home page for 
Prior art discovery  --  Company F was being sued for patent infringement.  ACE consultants identified prior art the patent of questions, thereby stopping the infringement suit.
marketing corporate products initiated.

<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Corporate alliances</STRONG>  --  Company H executives needed assistance in developing alliances 
for manufacturing and marketing throughout the Pacific Rim.  Strategies were considered, 
contacts were made anonymously, and options developed.  Assistance was provided to 
consummate the selected alliance.
<BR><BR>
<STRONG>Critical path technologies</STRONG> --  Company J executives were concerned that 
they did not control all of the technologies required by their strategic plan 
for next generation products.  A workshop developed a list of critical path 
technologies.  Determinations were made on technologies to develop in-house, and 
those to develop through contract.  Assistance was provided to identify technology 
options, and to negotiate rights to outsourced technologies.<BR><BR>
