<H2>THE SIERRA MADRE UNITED METHODIST CHURCH...</H2>

<H3>...Is a Christian fellowship seeking to share the love of Jesus Christ
through worship, service and evangelism.</H3>
<P>
<P>
<H2>OUR INTENT AS A CHRISTIAN COMMUNITY IS FOUR-FOLD:</H2>

<H3>
<OL>
<LI>To be a caring fellowship whose compassionate, non-judgmental attitude
invites and accepts all.</LI>
<LI>To awaken, nurture, and stimulate within each individual a response to
the Holy Spirit through education, study, worship, prayer, and fellowship.</LI>
<LI>To reach out in loving witness individually and collectively, responding
in concern to the needs of others.</LI>
<LI>To be loyal to God's church, and uphold it by our prayers, attendance, 
gifts, and services.</LI>
</OL>
</H3>
<HR>
<P>
<P>
<H2>COMMUNITY SERVICE AND OUTREACH</H2>

<H3>We Are Cooperating With Our Community Through:</H3>
<UL>
<STRONG><LI>12-Step Recovery Groups: AA, CA, GA, ACA for Men and Women in 
Sierra House Recovery Group Room</LI>
<LI>Pasadena City College Parent Education</LI>
<LI>Union Station</LI>
<LI>Friends in Deed</LI>
<LI>Community Support Services (formerly P.D.U.M.C.S.)</LI>
<LI>Senior Nutrition and Activities Program (S.N.A.P.)</LI></STRONG></UL>

