<HEAD>
<TITLE>Learning from Vegas, June 23, 1996</TITLE>
<META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Rich La Shure">
<META NAME="Keywords" CONTENT="Leaving Las Vegas movies religion 
                               Tillich Venturi unconditional love
                               Christianity Methodist salvation">
<META NAME="expiration" CONTENT="December 31, 1996">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<PRE>
<A HREF="/SMUMC/index.html"><H2>Return to Sierra Madre UMC home page.</H2></A>
<P>
LEARNING FROM VEGAS	SERMON BY REV. RICH LA SHURE
ROMANS 5.1-8	JUNE 23, 1996

	THE POSTMODERNIST ARCHITECT ROBERT VENTURI WROTE A BOOK ENTITLED 
LEARNING FROM LAS VEGAS. THE BOOK TOOK A TIMELY LOOK AT THE VARIOUS 
FORMS OF WEIRD, GLAMOROUS AND OUTRAGEOUS BUILDINGS IN THAT GLITTERING 
CITY OF THE NIGHT. VENTURI CONCLUDED THAT EVEN THOUGH LAS VEGAS 
ARCHITECTURE MAY SEEM TO BE GARISH, TASTELESS AND AS SHALLOW AS A 
TEASPOON, IT REPRESENTS WHAT AMERICANS REALLY LIKE, DEEP DOWN INSIDE.
	TWO WEEKS AGO I ASKED YOU TO CONSIDER DOING SOMETHING THAT I HAD 
NEVER BEFORE ASKED MEMBERS OF MY CONGREGATION TO DO: TO VIEW AN R-
RATED MOVIE TO PROVIDE THE BASIS FOR OUR MUTUAL UNDERSTANDING ON A 
SPECIFIC SUBJECT. PERSONALLY I SELDOM WATCH MOVIES THAT ARE RATED R, 
FOR OBVIOUS REASONS. THE OLDER I GET THE LESS INTERESTED I AM IN THE THINGS 
THAT TRIGGER THE R RATING. YET I FELT THAT IN THE CASE OF THE MOVIE LEAVING 
LAS VEGAS I NEEDED TO MAKE AN EXCEPTION. THIS WAS FOR TWO BASIC REASONS: 
FIRST, BECAUSE NICHOLAS CAGE WAS GIVEN THE ACADEMY AWARD FOR BEST 
PERFORMANCE BY AN ACTOR FOR HIS WORK IN LEAVING LAS VEGAS. WHAT THE 
ACADEMY CHOOSES AS ITS BEST IS USUALLY VIEWED BY A LARGE AUDIENCE OF 
PEOPLE. AND SECOND, BECAUSE THE ADVERTISING FOR THE MOVIE INCLUDED A KEY 
THEOLOGICAL TERM: UNCONDITIONAL ACCEPTANCE. 
	THE THEOLOGICAL WRITINGS OF UNION SEMINARY PROFESSOR PAUL TILLICH 
HAVE BEEN IMPORTANT TO ME SINCE MY OWN SEMINARY DAYS. IN SUCH 
COLLECTIONS OF SERMONS AS THE COURAGE TO BE, THE SHAKING OF THE 
FOUNDATIONS AND THE NEW BEING, AS WELL AS IN HIS 3-VOLUME SYSTEMATIC 
THEOLOGY, TILLICH OUTLINED THE GOSPEL OF JESUS CHRIST FOR A POST-RELIGIOUS 
AGE. WRITING FROM JUST AFTER WORLD WAR TWO THROUGH THE TUMULTUOUS 60S, 
TILLICH AIMED TO TRANSLATE BIBLICAL CONCEPTS INTO THE LANGUAGE OF A WORLD 
WHOSE FAITH IN GOD HAD BEEN SHAKEN TO ITS VERY FOUNDATIONS BY THE EVENTS 
OF THE HOLOCAUST. ANOTHER THEOLOGIAN BY THE NAME OF THOMAS J. J. ALTIZER 
LOOKED AT THE SAME EVENTS AND SOLEMNLY CONCLUDED THAT GOD WAS DEAD. OF 
THE TWO, TILLICH WAS MORE FAITHFUL. HE WAS WILLING TO ALLOW THAT 
SOMETHING OF GREAT SPIRITUAL IMPORTANCE HAD INDEED DIED ALONG WITH THE 6 
MILLION EUROPEAN JEWS AT THE HANDS OF THE NAZIS, BUT IT WASNT GOD. WHAT 
HAD DIED, PERHAPS, WAS HUMAN OBEDIENCE TO THE WILL OF THE GOD OF LOVE. 
AND IT IS UP TO CHRISTIANS IN EVERY AGE TO SEE IF TRUE OBEDIENCE TO GOD CAN 
BE RESURRECTED TO LIFE, AS JESUS WAS RESURRECTED.
	IN ONE OF HIS GREAT, RINGING PASSAGES, PAUL TILLICH PREACHED THE 
FOLLOWING: SOMETIMES A LIGHT BREAKS INTO OUR DARKNESS, AND IT IS AS 
THOUGH A VOICE WERE SAYING: YOU ARE ACCEPTED. YOU ARE ACCEPTED, BY THAT 
WHICH IS GREATER THAN YOURSELF AND THE NAME OF WHICH YOU DO NOT KNOW. 
DO NOT TRY TO DO ANYTHING NOW; PERHAPS LATER YOU WILL DO MUCH. DO NOT 
SEEK ANYTHING; DO NOT INTEND ANYTHING; DO NOT PERFORM ANYTHING. SIMPLY 
ACCEPT THE FACT THAT YOU ARE ACCEPTED.  IT SURPRISES ME THAT IN 1996, MORE 
THAN A QUARTER OF A CENTURY AFTER I FIRST READ THOSE WORDS, THEY 
IMMEDIATELY COME TO MIND WITHOUT MY HAVING TO LOOK THEM UP. AND I DO NOT 
HAVE A PHOTOGRAPHIC MEMORY; ITS JUST THAT THE PASSAGE CONTAINS A WHOLE 
WORLD OF MEANING FOR ME.
	IN THE WRITINGS OF PAUL TILLICH, THE INTERCHANGEABLE TERMS 
ACCEPTANCE AND UNCONDITIONAL LOVE APPEAR OVER AND OVER AGAIN. HE 
SPECIFICALLY USED THE TERM UNCONDITIONAL LOVE AS A MODERN TRANSLATION, 
A NEW SYNONYM FOR THE BIBLICAL TERM GRACE. UNCONDITIONAL LOVE MEANS 
THE GRACE OF GOD. WE LOVE GRACE. WE LOVE TO THINK ABOUT GRACE. WE LOVE 
TO HEAR ABOUT GRACE. WE LOVE TO SING ABOUT GRACE. THE MOST FREQUENTLY-
REQUESTED HYMN IN THE UNITED METHODIST CHURCH IS AMAZING GRACE. 
	GRACE IS THE UNDESERVED, UNEARNED, UNMERITED LOVE THAT THE CHILDREN 
OF GOD RECEIVE FROM GOD. GRACE IS THE LOVE OF THE FATHER WHO KEEPS THE 
CANDLE FLAME OF HOPE BURNING FOR HIS WAYWARD, PRODIGAL SON WHO 
DEMANDED HIS INHERITANCE EARLY AND THEN SQUANDERED HIS INHERITANCE ON 
LOOSE LIVING, THE LOVE OF THE FATHER WHO RUNS OUT TO MEET HIS SON ON THE 
WAY HOME, THROWS HIS ARMS AROUND HIM, AND REJOICES: THIS IS MY BELOVED 
SON, WHO WAS LOST, AND NOW IS FOUND; WHO WAS DEAD, AND IS NOW ALIVE! 
GRACE IS THE CARE OF THE GOOD SHEPHERD WHO LEAVES THE 99 MEMBERS OF HIS 
FLOCK SAFE ON THE HILLSIDE PASTURE AND GOES OUT SEARCHING FOR THE ONE 
LOST SHEEP. GRACE IS THE LORD JESUS CHRIST NAILED TO A HEAVY, ROUGH CROSS 
OF WOOD, MANAGING TO SAY WITH VIRTUALLY HIS DYING BREATH, FATHER, FORGIVE 
THEM, FOR THEY KNOW NOT WHAT THEY DO.  GOOD FRIENDS, CAN YOU SEE THAT 
YOU AND I DEPEND UPON THE GRACE OF GOD IN THE SAME WAY A SKYDIVER 
DEPENDS UPON HIS BACKUP PARACHUTE? AMEN?
	GRACE IS THE FORGIVENESS OF OUR SINS; GRACE IS THE ASSUMPTION OF OUR 
DEBTS; GRACE IS THE MENDING AND HEALING OF OUR BROKENNESS; GRACE IS THE 
AFFIRMATION OF OUR IDENTITIES; GRACE IS THE RESTORATION OF OUR 
RELATIONSHIPS. AND THE MODERN WAY OF SAYING GRACE IS UNCONDITIONAL 
LOVE. THAT HAS TOO MANY SYLLABLES TO BE EASILY SUNG IN A HYMN: AMAZING 
UNCONDITIONAL LOVE, HOW SWEET THE SOUND... SOMEDAY WHEN I AM INVITED TO 
SAY GRACE BEFORE A MEAL, IM GOING TO ASK EVERYONE TO BOW BEFORE I SAY 
UNCONDITIONAL LOVE. AMEN!
	WITH THIS AS MY BACKGROUND, I WAS NATURALLY INTRIGUED BY THE BLURB 
ON THE VIDEO BOX FOR THE MOVIE LEAVING LAS VEGAS. IT READS, FROM THE 
MOMENT BEN AND SERA (THE TWO MAIN CHARACTERS) CONNECT, THEY FORM A 
UNIQUE BOND BASED ON UNCONDITIONAL ACCEPTANCE AND MUTUAL RESPECT THAT 
WILL CHANGE EACH OF THEM FOREVER. I HAD TO SEE AND LEARN WHAT OUR 
CULTURE MEANS BY UNCONDITIONAL ACCEPTANCE.
	LEAVING LAS VEGAS IS, QUITE SIMPLY, A PORTRAIT OF TWO INDIVIDUALS IN 
HELL. BEN IS A SUCCESSFUL SCRIPT EXECUTIVE FOR A HOLLYWOOD FILM COMPANY, 
AND HE HAS IT ALL--THE BMW, THE SPLIT-LEVEL POOL HOME IN ENCINO, THE 
GORGEOUS BLOND WIFE AND THE GREAT SON. OR AT LEAST HE HAD THESE 
BLESSINGS UNTIL HE DRANK THEM AWAY. WHEN WE FIRST MEET HIM BEN IS BEING 
FIRED FROM HIS JOB BECAUSE OF HIS ALCOHOLISM. HIS WIFE HAS ALREADY LEFT HIM 
AND HAS TAKEN THE KID WITH HER. WE DONT KNOW ANY OF BENS REASONS FOR 
WASTING HIS OPPORTUNITIES, AND WE ARE NOT LET IN ON THEM AS THE STORY 
UNFOLDS. THAT IS A GOOD THING, REALLY, FOR EVERY MAN WHO HAS EVER DRAINED 
AWAY HIS FUTURE AT THE BOTTOM OF A BOTTLE HAS DONE SO WITH ALL THE BEST 
REASONS AND THE MOST PLAUSIBLE EXCUSES IN THE WORLD. ALL WE KNOW ABOUT 
BEN  IS THAT HE HAS LOST HIS WILL TO LIVE, AND HE HAS MADE UP HIS MIND TO MOVE 
TO LAS VEGAS AND DRINK HIMSELF TO DEATH. THERE IN THE GLITTERING CITY OF THE 
NIGHT, HE MEETS SERA, A YOUNG PROSTITUTE WHO HAS SEEN IT ALL AT LEAST 
TWICE. HE HIRES HER--NOT TO HAVE SEX, BUT JUST TO TALK, AND THIS IS HOW THEIR 
RELATIONSHIP BEGINS.
	RIGHT HERE I HAVE TO STOP AND SAY THAT THIS MOVIE CONTAINS SOME OF 
THE FOULEST LANGUAGE I HAVE EVER HEARD IN A FILM, AND IT CONTAINS SCENES 
THAT BORDER ON VIOLENT PORNOGRAPHY. IT REALLY PULLS NO PUNCHES AND 
THROWS IN NO ARTIFICIAL SWEETENERS. ITS VERY TOUGH TO WATCH ALL THE WAY 
THROUGH, AND IF YOU COULDNT MAKE IT, GOD BLESS YOU. IF YOU DID, GOD BLESS 
YOU, TOO. 
	BY AND BY, SERAS PIMP MEETS WITH A VIOLENT DEATH AND SO SHE BECOMES 
HER OWN BOSS. AT THE SAME TIME, HER AFFECTION FOR BEN GROWS TO THE POINT 
WHERE SHE INVITES HIM TO MOVE IN WITH HER. THEY ARE A VERY ODD COUPLE 
INDEED, WITH BEN DRINKING HIMSELF INTO TOTAL OBLIVION EVERY DAY AND SERA 
GOING OUT TO WALK THE STREETS EVERY NIGHT. HER CUSTOMERS RANGE FROM 
POLITE-SEEMING, WELL-DRESSED MEN TO VICIOUS CREEPS, AND SHE COMES OUT 
MUCH THE WORSE FOR WEAR.
	AT ONE POINT EARLY IN THEIR COHABITATION, BEN SPELLS OUT HIS CONDITION 
FOR STAYING WITH SERA: YOU MUST NEVER, NEVER ASK ME TO STOP DRINKING. IN 
HER TURN, SERA EXPECTS BEN NOT TO INTERFERE WITH HER PERFORMANCE OF HER 
CHOSEN CAREER. WHAT BINDS THEM TOGETHER IS THEIR SHARED, DESPERATE 
SENSE OF LONELINESS. IT IS WELL KNOWN THAT A PRIMARY MOTIVE OF ALCOHOLICS 
IS TO DISTANCE THEMSELVES FROM OTHER PEOPLE. LIKEWISE, SELLING SEX IS A WAY 
TO DE-PERSONALIZE THIS MOST HOLY OF OUR PHYSICAL GIFTS FROM GOD. BOTH BEN 
AND SERA HAVE MADE UP THEIR MINDS TO CHECK OUT AS FAR AS THE REST OF THE 
HUMAN RACE IS CONCERNED.
	AS TOUGH AS IT IS TO WATCH, LEAVING LAS VEGAS STILL HAS A HEART. YOU 
CARE ABOUT THESE PEOPLE; YOU WANT THEM TO TURN THEIR LIVES AROUND; YOU 
REALLY BELIEVE THAT THEY LOVE EACH OTHER, AND SOME OF THEIR TENDER 
MOMENTS TOGETHER ARE ACHINGLY ROMANTIC. YET THE STORY IS TOO REALISTIC 
TO HAVE A SUGARY HAPPY ENDING PASTED ONTO IT. THE SAD TRUTH IS THAT MOST 
PEOPLE WHO SET OUT TO DESTROY THEMSELVES SUCCEED.
	WHAT HAPPENS? AFTER A MONTH OF STEADY BINGE DRINKING, BEN FINALLY 
DEFEATS HIS BODYS ABILITY TO ABSORB MASSIVE QUANTITIES OF ALCOHOL. BINGE 
DRINKERS USUALLY DIE EITHER FROM ACUTE LIVER FAILURE OR FROM ANEURYSMS 
OF THE ESOPHAGUS OR THE STOMACH, LITERALLY DROWNING IN THEIR OWN BLOOD. 
SERA IS THERE WHEN BEN DIES, AFTER HE MUTTERS SOMETHING ABOUT PUTTING US 
ASUNDER, A TRAGIC ECHO OF THE WORDS FROM MATTHEW 19.6 WHICH ARE ALSO 
FOUND IN THE CHURCHS MARRIAGE CEREMONY. WE HEAR SERAS PERSPECTIVE ON 
HER RELATIONSHIP WITH BEN THROUGH VIGNETTES OF HER SPEAKING TO A 
THERAPIST. THESE ARE HER LAST LINES: I THINK THE THING US--WE BOTH REALIZED 
THAT WE DIDNT HAVE THAT MUCH TIME--AND I ACCEPTED HIM FOR WHO HE WAS. AND 
I DIDNT EXPECT HIM TO CHANGE--AND I THINK HE FELT THAT FOR ME TOO. I LIKED HIS 
DRAMA. AND HE NEEDED ME. I LOVED HIM...
	AND THAT, GOOD FRIENDS, IS WHAT OUR CULTURE MEANS BY UNCONDITIONAL 
ACCEPTANCE. TO ACCEPT SOMEONE FOR WHO THEY ARE, AND NEVER EXPECT THEM 
TO CHANGE. I SAY UNTO YOU THAT THIS IS NOT--REPEAT, THIS IS NOT GRACE--THIS IS 
NOT THE LOVE GOD GIVES US AND IT IS NOT THE LOVE GOD CALLS US TO HAVE FOR 
ONE ANOTHER.
	THE UNTOLD STORY OF LEAVING LAS VEGAS IS ALL THE OTHER PEOPLE LIKE 
BEN AND SERA. HENRY DAVID THOREAU SAID THAT THE MASS OF MEN LEAD LIVES 
OF QUIET DESPERATION. NOW PRAISE GOD THAT MOST REAL LIVES ARE MORE 
DISCIPLINED THAN THE LIVES OF MOVIE CHARACTERS, YET WE WOULD BE SHOCKED 
TO LEARN HOW MANY REAL LIVES ARE CAREENING OUT OF THEIR ORBITS. IN LAS 
VEGAS, IN LOS ANGELES, AND EVEN HERE IN THE PLEASANT NEIGHBORHOODS OF 
PASADENA, ARCADIA AND SIERRA MADRE, PEOPLE ARE PERISHING FROM 
LONELINESS AND THE HOPELESSNESS OF THINKING THAT NO ONE REALLY KNOWS 
THEM, AND IF THEY DID KNOW THEM, THEY WOULDNT LIKE THEM. FEELING SO 
VULNERABLE, FEELING SO DESPERATE FOR COMPANIONSHIP, TOO MANY OF US 
EXPECT TOO LITTLE OF OTHERS JUST AS WE EXPECT TOO LITTLE OF OURSELVES. 
AND YES, GOD LOVES REAL PEOPLE WHO ARE SINKING BENEATH THE WAVES JUST 
LIKE BEN AND SERA.
	THE GRACE OF GOD, REVEALED DECISIVELY BY JESUS CRUCIFIED, IS A LOVE 
THAT ACCEPTS US AS WE ARE AND PROVIDES US WITH THE RESOURCES TO CHANGE, 
TO CHANGE FOR THE BETTER, SO THAT WE MAY EXPERIENCE THE VERY BEST THAT 
LIFE HAS TO OFFER. IT IS THE LOVE OF A PARENT WHO WANTS THE VERY BEST FOR 
HIS OR HER BELOVED CHILD. CAN A LOVING PARENT STAND BY DULLY WHILE HIS OR 
HER CHILD LETS THE PROMISE OF LIFE SLIP THROUGH THEIR FINGERS? NO WAY! AS IT 
SAYS IN FIRST CORINTHIANS 13, LOVE BEARS ALL THINGS, LOVE BELIEVES ALL 
THINGS, LOVE HOPES ALL THINGS, LOVE ENDURES ALL THINGS... SURE--BUT DOES 
THAT IMPLY THAT LOVE DOES NOT CARE ABOUT SUCH THINGS? IT DOES NOT. YOU 
BETTER BELIEVE THAT LOVE CARES WHAT HAPPENS!
	OUR CULTURE HAS A COMMON AND WONDERFUL EXPRESSION FOR THE 
COMMITMENT LEVEL OF MODERN RELATIONSHIPS: ILL ALWAYS BE THERE FOR YOU. 
THATS GREAT; THATS ABOUT FIDELITY AND CONSISTENCY AND CONSTANCY. BUT 
THERE IS MORE TO LOVE THAN SIMPLY BEING PRESENT IN THE ROOM WHEN A LOVED 
ONE MANAGES TO DESTROY THEMSELVES. LOVE ALSO MUST BE WILLING TO 
INTERVENE FOR THE SAKE OF THE BELOVED.
	HERE IS THE CRUX OF OUR SCRIPTURE FOR TODAY, SO IMPORTANT A PART OF 
THIS SCRIPTURAL TEACHING THAT PAUL REPEATS IT TWICE, WITH SLIGHT VARIATION. 
WHILE WE WERE STILL WEAK, AT THE RIGHT TIME CHRIST DIED FOR THE UNGODLY.  
(VERSE 6) GOD SHOWS HIS LOVE FOR US IN THAT WHILE WE WERE SINNERS, CHRIST 
DIED FOR US. (VERSE 8) THIS IS LOVES INTERVENTION INTO THE DESTRUCTIVE 
PATTERN OF SIN. THROUGH JESUS CHRIST WE HAVE BEEN GIVEN EMERGENCY 
ACCESS TO THE GRACE OF GOD. SIMPLY BEING THERE FOR HIS CHILDREN WAS NOT 
ENOUGH FOR THE GOD OF INFINITE LOVE. GOD HAS ALWAYS BEEN AND ALWAYS WILL 
BE THERE FOR US. GOD LOVES US AS WE ARE. THATS A GIVEN. BUT IN HIS INFINITE 
COMPASSION GOD SAW THAT OUR PERSISTENCE IN SINNING REQUIRED A MORE 
DRAMATIC, MORE EFFECTIVE ACTION ON HIS PART. AND SO GOD INTERVENED.
	TWO WEEKS AGO, AS YOU MAY RECALL, WE LOOKED AT THE BRIDGE OF 
SALVATION THROUGH OUR LORD JESUS CHRIST. ITS PRINTED AGAIN IN YOUR 
SCRIPTURE NOTES FOR TODAY. THE FIRST KEY STEP IN CROSSING THAT BRIDGE 
FROM OUR SIDE TO GODS SIDE IS ACCEPTING JESUS AS OUR LORD AND SAVIOR, AS 
HE HAS ACCEPTED US. UNCONDITIONAL ACCEPTANCE IS NOT THE SAME THING AS 
RESIGNATION. THIS IS THE MESSAGE THAT WE HAVE GOT TO GET THROUGH TO 
PEOPLE WHO HAVE BEEN CONDITIONED BY CULTURE TO SETTLE FOR WAY TOO 
LITTLE, WAY TOO LATE. ONLY WHEN WE REALIZE HOW MUCH GOD DESIRES FOR OUR 
LIVES WILL BE BEGIN TO DESIRE MORE FOR OUR LIVES. AND HOW MUCH DOES GOD 
DESIRE FOR OUR LIVES? NOTHING LESS THAN ABUNDANT JOY, FULFILLING 
RELATIONSHIPS, PHYSICAL WHOLENESS, ETERNAL PEACE AND HEAVENLY REWARD. 	
	CAN WE LEARN SOMETHING FROM MOVIES LIKE LEAVING LAS VEGAS? YOU BET 
WE CAN, IF WE READ BETWEEN THE LINES. AND THE NUMBER ONE LESSON WE CAN 
LEARN IS HOW LOST WE ARE WITHOUT JESUS CHRIST. THIS I PROMISE YOU: THE SON 
OF GOD IS CAPABLE OF ENTERING ANY HUMAN RELATIONSHIP, NO MATTER HOW 
MESSED UP IT IS; HE IS CAPABLE OF ENTERING ANY HUMAN LIFE; HE IS CAPABLE OF 
ENTERING YOUR LIFE, AND TURNING IT AROUND WITH THE TRANSFORMING POWER OF 
UNCONDITIONAL LOVE. AMEN.
<P>
<A HREF="/SMUMC/index.html"><H2>Return to Sierra Madre UMC home page.</H2></A>
