<TITLE>Euterpe Opera Theatre</TITLE>
<META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Clyde E. Collins">
<META NAME="Keywords" CONTENT="opera theatre Euterpe musical comedy drama">
<BODY>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="Euterpe_t.gif"  HEIGHT=72,WIDTH=288, ALT="[Euterpe Logo]">
</CENTER>
<BR CLEAR='all'>

<IMG SRC="http://www.magicdragon.com/Euterpe1_t.gif" ALIGN='LEFT'></A>

Euterpe,<A HREF="http://www.fairfield.com/cyberspacecafe/museweek.html"> 
<STRONG>muse</STRONG> </A> of lyric poetry

<H3>Euterpe Opera Theatre is a small opera theatre company.  Founded in 1924, 
and based in Los Angeles, Euterpe Opera performs in English.</H3>
<UL>

<LI><A HREF="History.html"> <STRONG>History</STRONG> </A> of the Euterpe Opera Theatre<BR></LI><BR>
<LI>Euterpe Opera's <A HREF="Director.html"> <STRONG>Music Director</STRONG> </A>
 is Dr. Lois Musmann.</LI><BR><BR>
<LI>Euterpe Opera's<A HREF="NewProduction.html"> <STRONG>next production,</STRONG></A> 
in Summer and Fall, 1996, is "Berlin to Broadway with Kurt Weill."</LI><BR><BR>
<LI>Euterpe Opera's <A HREF="1997Production.html"><STRONG>1997 Comic opera</STRONG> 
</A>production<P>
<LI>Recent Euterpe Opera Theatre Productions:<BR>

<UL>
<LI>1993: Haydn's "Infidelity Foiled"</LI>
<LI>1994: Mozart's "Za&#239;de"</LI>
<LI>1995: Mozart's "Impresario" and Pergolesi's "La Serva Padrona"</LI>
</UL>

</LI><BR>

<LI><A HREF="Alumni.html"><STRONG>Alumn&#230;</STRONG> </A>and Alumni of Euterpe Opera</LI><BR>
</UL>
