<HTML>
<TITLE>Euterpe Music Director</TITLE>
<BODY>

<H2>Euterpe Opera's Music Director:</H2>


<P>Dr. Lois Musmann (Music Director and Conductor) graduated from the New 
England Conservatory of Music in Boston with a degree in performance of 
early music and harpsichord; and she was harpsichordist for the Chamber 
Orchestra of Cape Ann in Gloucester, MA.  She obtained her Master of Music 
in conducting from the University of Redlands in 1986, and her Doctor of 
Musical Arts degree from USC, in conducting, in 1989.  She has been on the 
adjunct faculty at Cal Poly Pomona and at the 
University of Redlands, and she is presently on the music faculty at the 
San Bernadino Valley College.  She prepared the chorus for last Summer's 
production of Bizet's <I>Carmen</I> at the Redlands Bowl.  She has conducted 
orchestras in Los Angeles, Santa Cruz, and San Diego.</P>
<P>
<A HREF="Dr_Lois.gif"><IMG SRC="Dr_LoisSmaller.gif">
Click to expand picture to full size (649K Gif).</A>

<P>Dr. Musmann has founded and conducts the Pacific Chamber Orchestra.  This 
chamber orchestra is used as the pit orchestra by Euterpe Opera Theatre</P>


<H2>About Pacifica Chamber Orchestra:</H2>


<P>The Pacifica Chamber Orchestra was founded in 1990, and often performs in 
settings of architectural interest.  The group, comprised of 30 players, 
has been recognized with grants awarded by the Riverside Arts Foundation.  
Though based in Riverside County, this group has also performed in Los 
Angeles, San Diego, and San Bernadino counties.</P>

<A HREF="framed.html">Return to Home Page</A>
</BODY>
