<TITLE>Euterpe Booking</TITLE>
<BODY>

<CENTER>
<H1><STRONG>Berlin To Broadway</STRONG></H1>
<H2>With Kurt Weill</H2>
</CENTER>

<UL>

<LI>A fully costumed and staged program of Cabaret Theatre</LI>

<LI>Offering Dates:  September, October, and November, 1996<BR>
In particular, <BR>
<P>
Monday, October 7, 1996<BR>
Opera 100, Laguna Hills.<P></LI>

<LI>Technical:  Uses full size stage,  extensive lighting,  props, minimal scenery
   with orchestra in pit.   Uses spot mikes for discrete sound enhancement 
   in larger auditoriums.  (No body mikes or mike stands used)</LI>

<LI>5 singers </LI>   

<LI>7 instruments:   reed (flute, clarinet, alto saxophone),  trumpet (double flugelhorn), guitar, 
   banjo, keyboard,  2 percussion;  and conductor.</LI>

<LI>2 Tech crew (stage manager and lighting board operator)</LI>

<LI>Cost to Venues:   $8000 first evening;  $7000 subsequent evenings</LI>
</UL>
<HR IMG SRC="/Net_Gifs/Bars/GreyNoteWhiteLineBlueBar.gif">
