<HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=450>

<H3><A NAME="N43_POL">CNSL N43 Policies</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI>Availability Completion Criteria (CLFINST 5400.2L)
    <UL>
    <LI>No C3/C4 CASREPs
    <LI>No C2 resulting from work done by yard, except items awaiting parts
    <LI>Must be capable of full power (ahead and astern)
    <LI>Successful boiler flex test and Combat Systems Integrated Test
    <LI>Satisfactory LOE and certifications
    <LI>Corrected Ship Selected Records given to Ship
    <LI>Completed Integrated Logistics Overhaul (if scheduled)
    </UL>
<LI>CASREP Policy
    <UL>
    <LI>CNSL Response Cell handles deployer CASREPS
    <LI>RSG/ISIC respond to CASREPs, CNSL act only when necessary
    <LI>CNSL tracks
    </UL>
<LI>Maximize ship self-sufficiency
    <UL>
    <LI>Accomplish maint. at lowest practical level
    <LI>Use IMAs vice depot when possible
    <LI>Message tech assists
    <LI>Onboard tech assists to assist/train S/F personnel
    <LI>Port Engineers facilitate/advocate
    </UL>
<LI>Support Industrial Base
<LI>Use TQL processes to develop recommendations for maintenance improvements
</UL>

<HR ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=450>

