<A NAME="RESTRICTIONS">
<B><FONT SIZE="+2">RESTRICTIONS... </A>
Some of the pages here are restricted to .navy.mil.</font></B>.<BR><BR>
<P>
Some of the pages here are restricted to .mil. This is to protect
government business sensitive information, or personal information
affecting the privacy of our employees.</P>

<P>If the computer that you are using is .navy.mil, yet is denied permission
to access the restricted pages, this is possibly due to a Domain Name Resolution
(meaning that your computer is not properly Internet-registered, and your
local systems administrator should be notified).
</P>

<A NAME="ALERTS">
<B><FONT SIZE="+2">VIRUS ALERTS... </A>
List of Selected NAVCIRT Advisories and DISN Security Bulletins</font></B>.<BR><BR>

<ul>
<LI><a href="/alerts/CONCEPT.HTM">
    Microsoft Word Macro "Concept" Virus Information</a>
        
<li><a href="/DISN/96-24.TXT">
     DISN 96-24 - Internet Hoaxes</a></li>

<li><a href="/NAVCIRT/96-015.TXT">
     NAVCIRT 08/96 - EXCELMACRO/LAROUX</a> - Affects Excell</li>

<li><a href="/NAVCIRT/96-009.TXT">
     NAVCIRT 05/96 - Trojan Horse Contained in PKZ300B</a></li>
<P>
          THIS TROJAN HORSE VIRUS HAS ALSO EMERGED ON THE INTENET WITH THE 
          NAME PKZIP300.ZIP, SO NAMED AS TO GIVE THE IMPRESSION THAT 
          THIS FILE IS A NEW VERSION OF THE PKZIP SOFTWRE USED TO 
          "ZIP" COMPRESSED FILES.  DO NOT DOWNLOAD THIS FILE UNDER ANY 
          CIRCUMSTANCES!!  IF YOU INSTALL OR EXPAND THE FILE, THE 
          VIRUS WILL WIPE YOUR HARD DISK CLEAN AND AFFECT MODEMS AT 
          14.4 AND HIGHER.  THIS VIRUS IS EXTREMELY DESTRUCTIVE AND 
          THERE IS NOT YET A WAY OF CLEANING THIS ONE UP.
</P>


</ul>

